15 001 608124001500 2017-10-01 Sun 10.1 - Perform dummy run with ROV and landed BOPs @ 21:33. Perfomed slump and overpull test. Test LBSR T/ 300/4;700 psi F/ 5/5 mins with 8.6 ppg sw.\r\n\r\nMon 10.2 - Continue to perform intial latch up tests. Transferred weight to tensioners.L/D landing joint and R/D riser ruuning tool. Subsea function BOP's F/ TCP yellow pod on 5 7/8" DP.Lay down double dutch. Wash and ream from 10;412' to 10;495'. Tagged cement at 10;495' with 10K. Displaced well to 11.4 ppg SBM (11.6 DHE). Drilled out cement plug from 10;495' to 10;835'. Circulated B/U. Wash and ream from 10;835' to 11;045'. TIH to 11;600' and circulate B/U.\r\n\r\nWed 10.4 - Continue to circulate B/U. Wash and ream. Pump a slug. POOH w/ 12 1/4" BHA. Tested 13 5/8" casing to 3;300 psi. P/U and RIH with EZSV packer and perf gun assembly. Set EZSV @ 11;489'. Tested backside to 1;000 psi-good test. Pressure up to 2;500 psi down DP - no indication gun fired. P/U 10' but no overpull was seen. Stung back into packer and confirmed shots fired while pumping down DP.\r\n\r\nThurs 10.5 - Attempted to establish injection rates - no success. R/D cement head. Pumped and spotted 25 bbls of high vis pill on top of the EZSV. POOH with EZSV running tool and L/D same. Tested EZSV to 1;000 psi. P/U and RIH with storm packer. Re-tested EZSV to 1;250 psi. Continue to RIH with storm packer. Set it at\r\n10;178'. Performed positive test and negative test.\r\n\r\nFri 10.6 - Performed negative test - Cementer bled off DPP from 1;764 psi to zero and monitored no flow for 30 minutes-good test. Reversed out 6.6ppg base oil. Pump slug and POOH to surface. Install gimbal and rig up remaining equipment. EDS unlatch LMRP @ 1523 hrs. R/U riser running equipment. F/T BLAT tool and P/U same. Made two attempts to latch with no success. L/D BLAT tool. Subsea torqued bolts on slip joint. P/U and M/U landing joint.\r\n\r\nSat 10.7 - Continue to prepare to pull riser. R/D drape hoses and storm loops. Pull and L/D landing joint. Pull riser from 9;509' to 9;059'. WOW.
16 001 608124001500 2017-10-08 Sun 10.8 - Transit back to original safe zone. Run riser and tested lines. Prepare and pick up slip joint; inspected and tested. M/U 10' pup. P/U landing joint. R/U drape hoses and storm loops in moonpool.\r\n\r\nMon 10.9 - Continue to R/U drape hoses and storm loops in moonpool. Test same. Move rig to well center. Latch BOPs and perform initial tests. L/D landing joint and R/D riser running equipment. Install diverter and R/D diverter running tool. R/U pipe handling equipment. P/U and RIH with storm packer running tool.\r\n\r\nTue 10.10 - Perform BOP Latch up tests. Sub Sea and Schlumberger test LMRP connector F/ DCP yellow pod 300 psi / 4;700 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 8.6 ppg sea\r\nwater-good test. Function test BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe F/ DCP yellow pod;\r\nSCP yellow pod; TCP blue pod. test UBSR 300/4;700 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 8.6 ppg sea water-good test. RIH with storm packer retrieval tool. Displace well and lines F/ 8.6 ppg seawater T/ 11.4 ppg SBM. Tag packer at 10;166' and attempt to unseat. Circulate bottoms up and unseat packer. Circulate bottoms up through choke/kill line @ 6 bpm; SPP-700 psi; MW-11.4 ppg; Note: Observed pack off; shutdown pumps. -Could not establish injection; move to procedure step 4b. POOH with RTTS to surface. POOH with BHA and service top drive.\r\n\r\nWed 10.11 - P/U TCP gun assembly and RIH with same to 10;435' MD (per step 4b upper perforation is 10;404' and lower perforation is 11;512'). Fire guns and flowcheck well. Wipe mill F/10;532' T/10;536'. POOH with TCP gun assembly. RIH with HES stinger.\r\n\r\nThurs 10.12 - RIH with stinger assembly and perform cement squeeze. Cement in place at 09:03. Total of 315 cubic feet pumped. ETOC of 11;266'. Unsting; circulate; and pump balanced plug on EZSV. Cement in place at 13:45. Total of 169 cubic feet pumped. Plug length: 200 feet. TOC 11;289'. POOH with stinger assembly. M/U bridge plug assembly and RIH with same.\r\n\r\nFri 10.13 - TIH with bridge plug to 500' above BOP. Pressure test cement plug to 1;250 psi-good test. RIH and set bridge plug at 10;304'. Positive test bridge plug to 1;250 psi-good test. Negative test cement plug-SLB continue to pump 188 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil & achieve a negative pressure of 1;800 psi; shut down pump when pressure\r\nachieved. Close MVBR's & test rams; apply 1;500 psi between rams. SLB bled pressure off in 500 psi increments to 0; Bled back-3 bbls. Monitor no flow for 30 mins (Good no flow).good test. Reverse out 188 bbl base oil. Displace well and lines to seawater. POOH with setting tool.\r\n\r\nSat 10.14 - POOH with bridge plug setting tool. R/U to unlatch BOP. Unlatch BOP. Funct BSRs.\r\n\r\nMMS Correspondence: \r\n*Verbal/e-mail correspondence McWilliams/Coco on 11/12/08 as follows:\r\nShell WR 508 #3 BP02 OCSG 17001- Extension of BOP pressure test on 4.1/2" DP\r\nMr Coco; \r\nWith reference to our recent conversation on the above subject. \r\nBackground \r\nThe Schlumberger MDT tool is currently in the hole on a mixed drill pipe string. We have been successful in acquiring pressures and samples and are currently about half way through the sampling program. The 14 day BOP test is due today and Schlumberger and Shell have concerns that if we pull out to test the BOP on 4.1/2" drill pipe then run back to continue the sampling program the samples may be at risk to seal failure due to cycling the external pressure on the tool.\r\n\r\nProposal \r\nOur proposal is to pull the MDT tool inside the 9.3/8" shoe; test the BOP on 6.5/8" drill pipe along with the auxilliary valves and surface equipment to meet the 14 day test requirement. Then test the BOP on 4.1/2" drill pipe on the way out of the hole with the MDT string which we anticipate to be on approximately November 15th. Our reasoning here is that we have a good overbalance in the hole (<1;000psi) and that in the unlikely event of a well control issue during the MDT program we would be closing the BOP on 6.5/8" drill pipe. The first time 4.1/2" drill pipe would be across the BOP would be when we retrieve the MDT string; at which point we are proposing to conduct the test.\r\n\r\nApproval \r\nI understand that you have given verbal approval to extend the BOP test on 4.1/2" drill pipe only; by 48 hours; to 2:30 PM on Friday November 14th. Prior to this time I will contact you and provide an update on the sampling program and a refined time on when we would expect to conduct the pressure test.\r\n\r\nAs per your request; we will note you verbal approval of the above on the IADC report. \r\nGrateful if you would confirm above by e-mail return. \r\n\r\n*11/12/08 e-mail reply Coco/McWilliam as follows: Confirmed.\r\n*11/14/08 e-mail McWilliam/Coco as follows: Reference our conversation; the rig has completed the current sampling program and preparing to pull out. This would mean testing the rams on 4.5" pipe tomorrow Sat November 15th.\r\n*11/14/08 e-mail Coco/McWilliam as follows: Extension granted until 11/15/2008.\r\n\r\n\r\n

Good test. Close SCSSV & pressure test to 500 psi for 15 minutes. no flow; (good test). Open SCSSV; break circulation; & begin packer fluid displacement per program.\r\n\r\nMon 07/23: Finish packer fluid displacement. Set production packer @ 27;313'MD / 25;948' TVD per procedure. Negative test production packer to 5000 psi; Packer's negative test was conducted for 15 minutes and no pressure build method was used. (good test). Negative test SCSSV to 2750 psi (good test). Positive test production packer to 3000 psi; Hold & chart for 15 minutes(good test). Close AAV and positive test same to 2000 psi (good test). Close SCSSV and monitor no flow for 15 minutes. Open LPR; release THRA from tubing hanger; & P/U to free travel. L/D circulating stand. U-tube 12.0 ppg CaBr2 out from kill line. Displace riser from 13.9 ppg CaBr2 to seawater. POOH w/ THRA F/ 9;588 T/ 6;034'.\r\n\r\nTues 07/24: POOH T/ surface w/ THRA & L/D. R/D Frank's equipment; IWOCS sheave; & Well Dynamics Sheaves. R/U riser equipment on rig floor to unlatch. Pull diverter.\r\n\r\nWed 07/25: R/U riser running tool; P/U landing joint; scope in slip joint & lock in. Transfer weight & unlatch BOP at 03:00 hrs. Move rig to safe zone & make heading change to latch up heading. ROV clean wellhead & prepare tree for land out. Land tree on THS at 10:20 hrs. ROV lock connector & perform pressure test to 9700 psi. ROV remove override tools from tree & align valves on tree. \r\n\r\n**all subsea testing was in PSIG units via ROV (9;611' water depth)\r\n\r\nInstallation tests are as follows:\r\n1)Gallery Test - 10;050 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes\r\n.\tPSV & ASV from Below\r\n.\tPMV from Above\r\n2)XT Tree Cap Test - 10;050 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes\r\n.\tPSV & ASV from Above\r\n.\tXT cap seals and Needle Valves from below\r\n3)PWV Test - 10;300 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes\r\n.\tPWV from Below\r\n.\tASV from above\r\n.\tPMV from above\r\n\r\nTree connector was tested via an external seal test after the connector was locked. The connector was tested to 10;425 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes. \r\n \r\nThurs 07/26: Move rig to safe zone. \r\n\r\nFri 07/27: Pull BOP on marine riser T/ surface. *** Operations Complete***\r\n

Wed 10.4 - Continue to circulate B/U. Wash and ream. Pump a slug. POOH w/ 12 1/4" BHA. Tested 13 5/8" casing to 3;300 psi. P/U and RIH with EZSV packer and perf gun assembly. Set EZSV @ 11;489'. Tested backside to 1;000 psi-good test. Pressure up to 2;500 psi down DP - no indication gun fired. P/U 10' but no overpull was seen. Stung back into packer and confirmed shots fired while pumping down DP.

Thurs 10.5 - Attempted to establish injection rates - no success. R/D cement head. Pumped and spotted 25 bbls of high vis pill on top of the EZSV. POOH with EZSV running tool and L/D same. Tested EZSV to 1;000 psi. P/U and RIH with storm packer. Re-tested EZSV to 1;250 psi. Continue to RIH with storm packer. Set it at
10;178'. Performed positive test and negative test.

Shell has permission to proceed with the Upper Pipe Ram in block. Good afternoon;
As discussed; we are requesting approval to deviate from the existing TA procedure.   We have pumped all three open hole plugs. The attempt to tag the top plug was unsuccessful. We are requesting approval to pull the cement stinger out of the hole and then trip in the hole with the 11-3/4" EZSV. We will then set the EZSV per the planned depth and attempt to pressure test below the EZSV to the approved test pressure of 2;000 psi. If the test is successful; we will proceed per the previously approved plan. If the test is unsuccessful; we will squeeze cement into the casing below the EZSV (approximately 42 bbls casing volume) to effectively isolate the casing shoe from the hole below.  At this point; we will proceed with the approved TA procedure.
Please let me know if you need additional information for review.  The previously approved procedure and schematic is attached.

MMS Correspondence: 
*Verbal/e-mail correspondence McWilliams/Coco on 11/12/08 as follows:
Shell WR 508 #3 BP02 OCSG 17001- Extension of BOP pressure test on 4.1/2" DP
Mr Coco; 
With reference to our recent conversation on the above subject. 
Background 
The Schlumberger MDT tool is currently in the hole on a mixed drill pipe string.  We have been successful in acquiring pressures and samples and are currently about half way through the sampling program. The 14 day BOP test is due today and Schlumberger and Shell have concerns that if we pull out to test the BOP on 4.1/2" drill pipe then run back to continue the sampling program the samples may be at risk to seal failure due to cycling the external pressure on the tool.

Proposal 
Our proposal is to pull the MDT tool inside the 9.3/8" shoe; test the BOP on 6.5/8" drill pipe along with the auxilliary valves and surface equipment to meet the 14 day test requirement.  Then test the BOP on 4.1/2" drill pipe on the way out of the hole with the MDT string which we anticipate to be on approximately November 15th.   Our reasoning here is that we have a good overbalance in the hole (<1;000psi) and that in the unlikely event of a well control issue during the MDT program we would be closing the BOP on 6.5/8" drill pipe.  The first time 4.1/2" drill pipe would be across the BOP would be when we retrieve the MDT string; at which point we are proposing to conduct the test.

Approval 
I understand that you have given verbal approval to extend the BOP test on 4.1/2" drill pipe only; by 48 hours; to 2:30 PM on Friday November 14th.   Prior to this time I will contact you and provide an update on the sampling program and a refined time on when we would expect to conduct the pressure test.

As per your request; we will note you verbal approval of the above on the IADC report. 
Grateful if you would confirm above by e-mail return. 

*11/12/08 e-mail reply Coco/McWilliam as follows: Confirmed.
*11/14/08 e-mail McWilliam/Coco as follows: Reference our conversation; the rig has completed the current sampling program and preparing to pull out. This would mean testing the rams on 4.5" pipe tomorrow Sat November 15th.
*11/14/08 e-mail Coco/McWilliam as follows: Extension granted until 11/15/2008.

Function test BOP from TCP on Yellow POD. Function test diverter in full auto sequence from DCP. Wash down and tag float collar at 26;392'. Drill out float collar; shoetrack; and 10' new formation while weighting up mud system. Pump out of hole into shoe and MWD pump up ESD of 13.66 (2x). Conduct FIT to 1;760psi surface pressure for 15ppg calculated EMW. 15.25bbls pumped/15.25bbls bled back. MWD pump up 14.89ppg ESD max. Drill ahead T/ 26;618' MD / 25;379' TVD while weighting up to 13.9ppg ESD.

Sun 05/13: Drill 12-1/4" hole section T/ 27;900'. Weight up from 13.7ppg DHEMW to 13.9ppg DHEMW at 27;150' MD.

Mon 05/14: Drill 12.25" hole T/ 30;011'. At 30;011'; pump 100 bbl Hi-Vis sweep and circulate.

Tues 05/15: Drill ahead T/ 30;131' MD / 28;272' TVD(Well TD). Pump out of hole and begin taking formation pressures as per program with Baker TesTrak.

Wed 05/16: Pump out of hole; collecting formation pressure samples as per program with Baker TesTrak. Max PP observed was 13.9ppg @ sensor depth of 28;290' MD / 26;753' TVD. Continue to pump out of hole 

Thurs 05/17: Function tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from TCP on Blue POD. Continue pumping out of hole and close BSRs. Function Test Diverter on 5-7/8" DP from TCP 

Fri 05/18: With BSRs closed; POOH T/ Surface. RIH with 10-1/8" casing stands out of derrick T/ 9;122'.

Sat 05/19: Monitor well below closed UBSR. Begin RIH with 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing T/ 20;314'. R/D casing handling equipment and R/U DP handling equipment and OES flowback tool. P/U and M/U 10-3/4" casing hanger and seal assembly as per FMC.

***REGULATORY: On 5/19/18 there was a minor leak observed coming from a vent line on blue pod following an ROV inspection. Mrs. Rachael Sandford with Shell Engineering received approval @ 20:21 hrs. from Mr. Bobby Nelson of BSEE Houma District to continue operations of running casing and performing the primary cement job as planned.

Sun 05/20: Continue rigging up DP handling equipment and begin running in hole with 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing on 6-5/8" 60# LS. RIH T/ 29;836'; and tagged up with 90K weight down. R/B stand; pick up string to 29;721'; and continue to work pipe while circulating bottoms up.

Mon 05/21: Flow check (well static). Wash down 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing string on 60# landing string T/ 30;008' MD / 28;171' TVD. 

Tues 05/22: Perform cement job per Halliburton procedure with 16.2 ppg Class H; 926 cubic feet of cement. Set seal assembly & test to 7000 psi per FMC procedure (good test). Circulate riser. POOH w/ landing string 

A. Explanation of lost returns (full loss; partial loss; etc) - partial; 1270 bbl lost during the cement job (1921 bbl pumped)
B. Were there any operational issues - losses
C. How was loss of returns indicated - returns in the pits
D. How much cement was pumped versus approved in APD - 926 cu ft pumped; 769 cu ft in APD
E. What was lift pressure - 100 psi
F. What is TOC and how has this been calculated - 28;550 MD/ 26;986 ft TVD by logging with SBT on wire


Wed 05/23:  P/U FMC LIT & 6-5/8" tail pipe and RIH on 5-7/8" DP. Function test BOP's on 6-5/8" tail pipe. L/O LIT and take impression per FMC. POOH T/ surface w/ FMC LIT & tail pipe; function diverter on way out.

Thurs 05/24: R/U wireline; P/U sonic tool string; & RIH T/ 29;770'. Perform sonic log. POOH w/ wireline T/ surface & L/D toolstring. Pressure test casing to 3000 psi (good test). P/U CIBP assy & RIH on 5-7/8" DP w/ FMC wear bushing. RIH

Fri 05/25:  Finish RIH w/ CIBP and set at 28;660' MD/ 27059 TVD. Tag w/ 15k down to verify. POOH 

*** Verbal Approval by Mr. Bobby Nelson regarding changes in CFlex Procedure

Sat 05/26: P/U C-flex cementing tool & RIH T/ 27;318'. Pressure test cups (good test). Latch into C-flex at 27;403' MD/ 26;022' TVD bit depth. Attempt to open C-flex; no indication. Attempt to inject and gain in trip tank.

Sun 05/27: Open C-flex and attempt to inject at 0.5 bpm (2940 psi max pressure). Shear solid seat in C-flex tool & circulate B/U. Perform unofficial casing test to 5000 psi (good test). Open C-flex & take injection pressures. Close C-flex and circulate B/U.

Mon 05/28: Open C-flex & establish injection rates. Perform cement job and squeeze 16.2 ppg Class H cement; 808 cubic feet of cement. Strip up & attempt to close C-flex with no success. Continue attempting to close C-flex. Able to engage & close. Bleed off pressure to confirm closed. Reverse circulate 1.5x string vol. Drop Archer dart & pump down. Attempt to latch into C-flex to permanently lock (no success). Attempt to shear out dart (no success). Pump slug & POOH. 

Tues 05/29: P/U 8-1/2" clean out BHA & RIH 

Wed 05/30: Continue RIH w/ 8-1/2" clean out assy T/ 28;190' & set down 20k. Wash & ream down T/ EZSV at 28;657'. Drill out EZSV. Wash & ream down to landing collar at 29;770' and tag w/ 10k down. Circulate B/U to WH. Function test BOP's & diverter. Continue circulating B/U to surface.

*Verbal approval from Mr. Adriano Garcia regarding BOP stack 1 Yellow Pod

Thurs 05/31: Finish circulating B/U & POOH T/ surface w/ 8-1/2" clean out assembly. R/U Baker wireline & P/U EZSV. RIH w/ EZSV on wireline and set at 29;757' MD/ 27;963' TVD.

Fri 06/01: POOH w/ EZSV setting tool. Test casing to 6500 psi for 30 min (good test). Function UBSR & LBSR. RIH w/ SBT wireline toolstring & perform SBT log. POOH w/ SBT toolstring. RIH w/ 5-7/8" DP to test BOP's.

**Verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson for setting of lockdown bushing

Sat 06/02: Pressure & function test BOP's. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200 psi. Tested rams and all related valves to 250/6500 psi from Halliburton unit with 13.7 ppg surface mud weight (14.06 ppg downhole mud weight) as per TOI procedure monitoring test pressures with EZ chart software. Pressure & function test performed on Yellow Pod from TCP Panel. Function test diverter from DCP. POOH & P/U FMC lock down assy. RIH

***Verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson for TA for THS

Sun 06/03: RIH w/ FMC lock down assy. Land out w/ 50k down & pressure up to 7500 psi to set. Take 50k overpull to confirm set. Release FMC RT; POOH; & L/D FMC RT. P/U RTTS assy & RIH w/ 3075' tail pipe below. Set RTTS at 10;685' & perform positive pressure test to 1000 psi (good test). Unable to release from RTTS. Unset RTTS; POOH; & change out overshot.

Mon 06/04: RIH w/ RTTS & set at 10;685'. Release from RTTS & positive test to 1000 psi. Negative test to 200 psi below seawater gradient w/ 197 bbls of base oil. Monitor no flow for 30 minutes. Good test. U-tube base oil out. Displace well above RTTS to seawater. POOH T/ surface w/ RTTS running tool.

Tues 06/05: P/U BLAT tool and transfer weight from MRT's to top drive and unlatch BOP's @ 03:45hrs. Land THS with #2 crane @ 08:30hrs. Unable to get test on THS. Troubleshoot THS test failure.

Wed 06/06:  Continue to troubleshoot THS test failure.

Thurs 06/07:   ROV tested THS connector to 10;300 psi gauge pressure (good test). Land and latch BOP on THS @ 14:36 hrs. P/U RTTS retrieval tool and RIH w/ same. Land FMC tool in THS and test BOP/THS connector against LBSR and UBSR to 250psi low / 9;100psi high. POOH 

Fri 06/08: Finish POOH. RIH w/ Halliburton RTTS overshot T/ 10;650'. Displace seawater above RTTS to 13.7ppg surface wt
SBM while monitoring barrel in / barrel out. Latch onto RTTS; retrieve to surface; and L/D same. POOH 

Sat 06/09: Finish POOH. P/U and M/U Halliburton clean out assemblies and RIH w/ same T/ 26;809'. Function test BOP from TCP on Blue POD. Function test diverter from TCP.

Sun 06/10: Continue RIH w/ Halliburton clean out assembly T/ 29;757'. Tag EZSV @ 29;759'. Displace Choke; Kill; and Boost to 13.9ppg brine to displace well.

*On 06/10/2018 @ 15:15hrs; Mrs. Lisa Lorenz (Shell Regulatory) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE Houma District) to add negative test of production casing in brine to procedure.

Mon 06/11: Continue displacing well to 13.9ppg CaBr2. POOH w/ WBCO assembly. Observed overpull with MagTech assembly through THS. Pull to surface and recover debris. Continue to POOH.

Tues 06/12:  Finish POOH. RIH with clean out assembly to 29;404' and activate jet sub. Jet BOP and function BOP from DCP on Yellow POD. Re-jet BOP and function diverter from DCP. Drop ball to de-activate jet sub and RIH to tag CIBP at 29;759' DP measurement.

Wed 06/13:  Reverse circulate through HPDU. Perform negative test on production casing by pumping 280 bbls of drill water and pressuring up to 3;000psi differential. Close test rams; bleed off pressure (11 bbls back). Monitor negative pressure test for no flow. Observe no flow from 20:00 to 20:30hrs. Good test. Rig down negative test lines and begin POOH 

Thurs 06/14:   Continue to POOH; Remove debris from magtech and Vali-tech assy; 35lbs of recovered from Vali-tech; 30lbs from magtech. NOTE: recovered chain from chain tongs off tools. Service rig floor equipment and clean same. P/u Halliburton clean well assy and RIH for second clean out run.

Fri 06/15: Continued TIH; Slip & Cut 1;700' of drill line


Sat 06/16: Function BOP's and wash C-flex; Tag bridge plug @ 29757'; Flow check well and POOH; Inspected mag techs and vali techs; R/U wireline

Sun 06/17: M/U and RIH with sump packer; Correlate and attempt to set with no success; POOH; Sump packer was pulled back to surface; P/U sump packer and RIH.

Mon 06/18: Continue TIH with sump packer 

Tues 06/19: Set sump packer at 29;475' MD / 27;731' TVD. Pump slug & POOH to test BOP's. Pressure test BOP's from Halliburton unit with 13.9 ppg CaBr2. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200 psi. Tested rams and all related valves to 250/6500 psi. Test performed on Blue Pod from Drillers Panel.

Wed 06/20: Completed BOP testing with 13.9 ppg CaBr2 as per TOI procedure monitoring test pressures with EZ chart software. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200 psi. Tested rams and all related valves to 250/6500 psi. Test
performed on Blue Pod from Drillers Panel; Functioned BOP's and Diverter on 4-1/2" drill pipe from Toolpushers Panel; Yellow Pod.; POOH with sump packer setting tool
 
Thurs 06/21:   R/U to P/U TCP assembly. P/U TCP assembly & RIH on 5-7/8" DP

Fri 06/22: Continue RIH with TCP assembly T/ 29;475'. Snap into sump packer and space out guns. Set packer; Close annular and apply 500 psi on top of packer. Perform firing sequence and observed DP pressure fall off indicating guns fired. Circulate at 2 bpm to establish loss rate (inital 120 bph; decrease to 30 bph). Shut down pumps and open bypass.  Static loss rate of 16 bph. Begin reverse circulation at 3 bpm.

Perfs:
HU1: 27999-28140 MD / 26513-26628 TVD
HU2U: 28248-28389 MD / 26719-26835 TVD
HU2L: 28499-28640 MD / 26925-27041 TVD
HU3: 28751-28892 MD / 27132-27247 TVD
HU4: 29010-29151 MD / 27346-27462 TVD
HU5: 27324-29465 MD / 27606-27721 TVD

Sat 06/23: Finish reverse circulating. Monitor losses (6-8 bbl/hr) and R/D surface iron. POOH w/ TCP assembly circulate. B/U through choke (no gas or contamination observed). Continue POOH 

Losses:  196 bbls

Sun 06/24: Continue POOH w/ TCP assy. Close LBSR & boost riser volume while monitoring well on trip tank (6 bbl/hr losses). Continue POOH and L/D TCP assy. P/U deburr BHA & RIH.

Mon 06/25: Continue RIH w/ Deburr BHA to top of perfs. Land out no go locator at 29;617' bit depth. Circulate brine. POOH above perfs & drop Churchill dart. Continue POOH 

Tues 06/26: POOH T/ surface and function test BOP's on 5-7/8" pipe from Toolpusher Control Panel on Blue pod & Diverter from TCP in full auto sequence; on way out.  R/U to run ESTMZ lower completion.

Wed 06/27:  P/U and RIH w/ ESTMZ zones 6; 5; 4; & 3 and pressure test each to 250 psi (all good tests). P/U and RIH w/ ESTMZ zone 2.
 
Thurs 06/28:  P/U & RIH w/ ESTMZ zones 2 & 1 and pressure test each to 250 psi (good tests). RIH w/ 4" wash pipe & latch in STT. POOH w/ 4" wash pipe & pressure test system to 250 psi in sump test position (good test). Confirm space out of lower service tool & pressure test system to 250 psi in RIH position (good test). P/U VCH packer assy; 2 stds of 4-1/2" DP; bundle carrier; 8 stds 5-7/8" DP; & BSRTT assy. RIH on 5-7/8" DP 

Fri 06/29: RIH w/ ESTMZ & BSRTT assy. Land out BSRTT and release. P/U above BOP and pressure test BSR's to 6500 psi. Function BSR's. Retrieve BSRTT and POOH. L/D BSRTT & RIH w/ ESTMZ assy 

Sat 06/30: RIH w/ ESTMZ assy to sump packer. Sting in; sting out to confirm depth. Set VCH packer per procedure BSRITT set at 27;905.71' MD / 26;435' TVD. perform 1500 psi pressure test on backside to confirm set (good test). Set isolation packers per procedure. Pressure test 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing for 30 min to 6500 psi (good test). Establish tool positions per Halliburton & pressure test service tool (good test). P/U frac head and R/U frac iron.

Sun 07/01: R/U frac iron & test w/ cement unit (good test). Perform pickle job. Pressure test lines again from Stim Star IV to frac head to 14;500 psi (good test). 

Mon 07/02: Perform main frac on zone HU5B. Pull up to zone HU4. test lines to 7;000 psi (good test).

Tues 07/03: Pump frac job for HU4. Early screen out and reverse circulate proppant. Function test BOP from DCP on Yellow POD. Function test diverter from DCP.

***Verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson to proceed with operations with Yellow Pod SEM B HPHT reading inaccuracies

Wed 07/04: Space out and establish tool positions for stimulation of HU3. Perform main frac on zone HU3. 
 
Thurs 07/05: Pull up to zone HU2L Establish tool positions with frac head installed.  Standby while MV Stim Star IV troubleshoots DP issues.

Fri 07/06: Complete troubleshooting/repairs of DP system on frac boat. 

Sat 07/07:  Pump main frac on zone HU2L. Close MCS and test MCS/FCS sleeves to 1;000psi (good test). POOH to zone HU2U.

Sun 07/08: Close MCS and test to 1;000 psi to verify closed. Monitor pressures while cleaning; flushing; and re-filling MGS with 13.9 ppg CaBr2. With LAP closed; open MCS and monitor pressures. Apply 1500 psi to backside and begin bullheading with cement unit at 9 bpm and 3;360 psi. Pumped a total of 1;361 bbls.

Mon 07/09: Continue to bullhead for a total volume of 1;361 bbls. Close MCS and test. Test below zone HU2 (good test) and above zone HU2 (no test). Reverse circulate workstring volume 

Tues 07/10: Pressure test closed MCS to 2;000psi (good test). Monitor pressures while pumping down DS to maintain wellhead pressure. Function test BOPs F/ DCP on Blue POD. Function test Diverter from TCP. 

***Verbal approval to test BOP's on 6" until able to test 4.5" given by Mr. Bobby Nelson

Wed 07/11: Space out to test BOP's on 6-5/8" StimTech joints. Pause testing to run service tool through Zone 1 (HU1) FCS and MJPS and observe TT become static after close shifter passed FCS. Pressure test system to 1;500psi (good test). RIH 2 stands and test well system to 1;500psi (good test). Re-trip MCS and FCS in Zone 2 (HU2U) and pressure test well system to 1;500psi (good test). Pick up side entry sub and rig up test lines. Resume BOP testing.
 
Thurs 07/12: Finish testing BOP's to 250 low /6500 high on both ram and annular and choke manifold. Begin main frac job on HU2U 

Fri 07/13: Complete main frac job on Zone HU2U. Close MCS and test same to 2;500psi.  POOH to zone HU1 and establish tool positions. P/U frac head and install in string. Pressure test surface lines and frac head to 14;500psi. Begin frac job on HU1.

Sat 07/14:  Finish main frac on Zone HU1 as per Halliburton pump schedule. Pressure test closed MCS to 1;500 psi (good test). Begin pressure testing BOP's on 4-1/2" pipe.

Sun 07/15: Pressure test BOP's on 4-1/2" DP. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200psi - Rams and all related valves to 250/6500psi from Halliburton unit with 13.9 ppg surface weight and related valves from DCP on Blue POD. Function test BOP from TCP on Blue POD. POOH with ESTMZ service tool F/ 11;457' - T/ surface and L/O same. Hold safety meeting; hang off block; and begin change out of drill line spool.

Mon 07/16:  Pick up and RIH with Halliburton production isolation assembly.

Tues 07/17: Continue RIH w/ Halliburton PIS assembly T/ 26;347'. Landed WBRT at 26;347' bit depth.& sheared out inner mandrel. Observed Fas Fill trip closed & pressure test down string to confirm (good test). Continue RIH T/ 27;892' .

Wed 07/18: RIH & shift open lower completion sleeves while monitoring losses and latch into VCH packer. Pressure test backside to 1000 psi for 30 min (good test). Pressure up down string to 2000 psi to release from PO tool. Reverse circulate 100 bbls to fill string. S/O to re-engage seals into PBR & pressure test FS2 (set at 27;848' MD / 26;387' TVD) down string to 1000 psi for 30 min (good test). Function test BOP's & diverter. POOH & pull wear bushing. Drop activation ball and jet BOP's & THS. Drop deactivation ball & boost riser. POOH F/ 24;484' T/ 5;400'.
 
Thurs 07/19: POOH T/ surface & L/D PO tool. Service rig equipment & R/U Frank's for upper completion. P/U & M/U upper completion assemblies & RIH. P/U CIM assy; terminate; & pressure test (good test). P/U PDPG assy; terminate; & pressure test (good test). RIH w/ production tubing F/ 890' T/ 3;627'.

Fri 07/20: RIH w/ production tubing T/ 3;627' T/ 15;104'. P/U & M/U SCSSV assy; terminate control lines; & pressure test SCSSV with Well Dynamics Unit to 15;000 psi for 15 minutes as per program (good test). RIH w/ production tubing T/ 18;193'. P/U & M/U FMC tubing hanger assy.

Sat 07/21:  Terminate control lines to FMC tubing hanger & test to 15;000 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Pressure test SV1 and SV2 control lines (internal test) to 12;500 psi for 15 minutes (good test). Connected the TEC cable head at bottom of tubing hanger. Pressure tested cable head interface to 15;000 psi for 15 minutes (good test).. P/U THRA. Flush lines & test. RIH w/ spanner joint & connect flat pack lines. Pressure test flat pack to SCSSV to 12;000 psi for 15 minutes. R/U to RIH on landing string. RIH F/ 18;282' T/ 19;538' on landing string.

Sun 07/22:  Continue RIH w/ upper completion on landing string T/ 27;805'. Land; set; & test tubing hanger seals to 13;100 psi for 15 minutes. No pressure build. Good test. Close SCSSV & pressure test to 500 psi for 15 minutes. no flow; (good test). Open SCSSV; break circulation; & begin packer fluid displacement per program.

Mon 07/23: Finish packer fluid displacement. Set production packer @ 27;313'MD / 25;948' TVD per procedure. Negative test production packer to 5000 psi; Packer's negative test was conducted for 15 minutes and no pressure build method was used. (good test).   Negative test SCSSV to 2750 psi (good test). Positive test production packer to 3000 psi; Hold & chart for 15 minutes(good test). Close AAV and positive test same to 2000 psi (good test). Close SCSSV and monitor no flow for 15 minutes. Open LPR; release THRA from tubing hanger; & P/U to free travel. L/D circulating stand. U-tube 12.0 ppg CaBr2 out from kill line. Displace riser from 13.9 ppg CaBr2 to seawater. POOH w/ THRA F/ 9;588 T/ 6;034'.

Tues 07/24: POOH T/ surface w/ THRA & L/D. R/D Frank's equipment; IWOCS sheave; & Well Dynamics Sheaves. R/U riser equipment on rig floor to unlatch. Pull diverter.

Wed 07/25: R/U riser running tool; P/U landing joint; scope in slip joint & lock in. Transfer weight & unlatch BOP at 03:00 hrs. Move rig to safe zone & make heading change to latch up heading. ROV clean wellhead & prepare tree for land out. Land tree on THS at 10:20 hrs. ROV lock connector & perform pressure test to 9700 psi. ROV remove override tools from tree & align valves on tree. 

**all subsea testing was in PSIG units via ROV (9;611' water depth)

Installation tests are as follows:
1)Gallery Test - 10;050 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes
.	PSV & ASV from Below
.	PMV from Above
2)XT Tree Cap Test - 10;050 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes
.	PSV & ASV from Above
.	XT cap seals and Needle Valves from below
3)PWV Test - 10;300 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes
.	PWV from Below
.	ASV from above
.	PMV from above

Tree connector was tested via an external seal test after the connector was locked.  The connector was tested to 10;425 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes.   
 
Thurs 07/26:  Move rig to safe zone. 

Fri 07/27: Pull BOP on marine riser T/ surface.  *** Operations Complete***

Perfomed slump and overpull test. Test LBSR T/ 300/4;700 psi F/ 5/5 mins with 8.6 ppg sw.

Mon 10.2 - Continue to perform intial latch up tests. Transferred weight to tensioners.L/D landing joint and R/D riser ruuning tool. Make up and install diverter. F/T diverter and L/D riser running equipment. C/O bails and install elevators. P/U and TIH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA.

Tue 10.3 - Test BOPs on 5 7/8" drill pipe on Blue pod; F/ Drillers station; all test performed with 8.6 ppg sw to 300/4;700psi for 5min each-good tests. Subsea function BOP's F/ TCP yellow pod on 5 7/8" DP.Lay down double dutch. Wash and ream from 10;412' to 10;495'. Tagged cement at 10;495' with 10K. Displaced well to 11.4 ppg SBM (11.6 DHE). Drilled out cement plug from 10;495' to 10;835'. Circulated B/U. Wash and ream from 10;835' to 11;045'. TIH to 11;600' and circulate B/U.

Wed 10.4 - Continue to circulate B/U. Wash and ream. Pump a slug. POOH w/ 12 1/4" BHA. Tested 13 5/8" casing to 3;300 psi. P/U and RIH with EZSV packer and perf gun assembly. Set EZSV @ 11;489'. Tested backside to 1;000 psi-good test. Pressure up to 2;500 psi down DP - no indication gun fired. P/U 10' but no overpull was seen. Stung back into packer and confirmed shots fired while pumping down DP.

Thurs 10.5 - Attempted to establish injection rates - no success. R/D cement head. Pumped and spotted 25 bbls of high vis pill on top of the EZSV. POOH with EZSV running tool and L/D same. Tested EZSV to 1;000 psi. P/U and RIH with storm packer. Re-tested EZSV to 1;250 psi. Continue to RIH with storm packer. Set it at
10;178'. Performed positive test and negative test.

Fri 10.6 - Performed negative test - Cementer bled off DPP from 1;764 psi to zero and monitored no flow for 30 minutes-good test. Reversed out 6.6ppg base oil. Pump slug and POOH to surface. Install gimbal and rig up remaining equipment. EDS unlatch LMRP @ 1523 hrs. R/U riser running equipment. F/T BLAT tool and P/U same. Made two attempts to latch with no success. L/D BLAT tool. Subsea torqued bolts on slip joint. P/U and M/U landing joint.

Sat 10.7 - Continue to prepare to pull riser. R/D drape hoses and storm loops. Pull and L/D landing joint. Pull riser from 9;509' to 9;059'. WOW."},{"   ":16,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608124001500,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-10-08","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 10.8 - Transit back to original safe zone. Run riser and tested lines. Prepare and pick up slip joint; inspected and tested. M/U 10' pup. P/U landing joint. R/U drape hoses and storm loops in moonpool.

Mon 10.9 - Continue to R/U drape hoses and storm loops in moonpool. Test same. Move rig to well center. Latch BOPs and perform initial tests. L/D landing joint and R/D riser running equipment. Install diverter and R/D diverter running tool. R/U pipe handling equipment. P/U and RIH with storm packer running tool.

Tue 10.10 - Perform BOP Latch up tests. Sub Sea and Schlumberger test LMRP connector F/ DCP yellow pod 300 psi / 4;700 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 8.6 ppg sea
water-good test. Function test BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe F/ DCP yellow pod;
SCP yellow pod; TCP blue pod. test UBSR 300/4;700 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 8.6 ppg sea water-good test. RIH with storm packer retrieval tool. Displace well and lines F/ 8.6 ppg seawater T/ 11.4 ppg SBM. Tag packer at 10;166' and attempt to unseat. Circulate bottoms up and unseat packer. Circulate bottoms up through choke/kill line @ 6 bpm; SPP-700 psi; MW-11.4 ppg; Note: Observed pack off; shutdown pumps. -Could not establish injection; move to procedure step 4b. POOH with RTTS to surface. POOH with BHA and service top drive.

Wed 10.11 - P/U TCP gun assembly and RIH with same to 10;435' MD (per step 4b upper perforation is 10;404' and lower perforation is 11;512'). Fire guns and flowcheck well. Wipe mill F/10;532' T/10;536'. POOH with TCP gun assembly. RIH with HES stinger.

Thurs 10.12 - RIH with stinger assembly and perform cement squeeze. Cement in place at 09:03. Total of 315 cubic feet pumped. ETOC of 11;266'. Unsting; circulate; and pump balanced plug on EZSV. Cement in place at 13:45. Total of 169 cubic feet pumped. Plug length: 200 feet. TOC 11;289'. POOH with stinger assembly. M/U bridge plug assembly and RIH with same.

Fri 10.13 - TIH with bridge plug to 500' above BOP. Pressure test cement plug to 1;250 psi-good test. RIH and set bridge plug at 10;304'. Positive test bridge plug to 1;250 psi-good test. Negative test cement plug-SLB continue to pump 188 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil & achieve a negative pressure of 1;800 psi; shut down pump when pressure
achieved. Close MVBR's & test rams; apply 1;500 psi between rams. SLB bled pressure off in 500 psi increments to 0; Bled back-3 bbls. Monitor no flow for 30 mins (Good no flow).good test. Reverse out 188 bbl base oil. Displace well and lines to seawater. POOH with setting tool.

Sat 10.14 - POOH with bridge plug setting tool. R/U to unlatch BOP. Unlatch BOP. Transit to Stones 4 Safe Zone and begin Stones 4 abandonment. Subject: Noble Danny Adkins; WR507 Well 1
Tracy;
Shell has permission to proceed with the Upper Pipe Ram in block.  It is our understanding that the 6 5/8" drill pipe will be protected with the fixed Middle Pipe Ram and the Lower VBR; and the 5" pipe will be protected with the Lower VBR (in addition to the Annulars and Shears).  It is also our understanding that the 5" pipe will not be across the BOP stack during drilling operations.   The Upper Pipe Ram must be clearly labeled as out of service at all control panels; and all personnel involved in well control must be notified that the Upper Pipe Ram is out of service.  Please ensure that all personnel involved in drilling operations/well control operations are clear on any potential changes this has to your well control procedures.  Also; please email me a copy of the BOP test once testing is complete.  If there are any further issues with functionality of the BOP stack please contact us immediately.
Josh Ladner

Subject: WR 507 OCSG 18730 001 ST 00 BP 00 - TA Deviation Request 
Good afternoon;
As discussed; we are requesting approval to deviate from the existing TA procedure.   We have pumped all three open hole plugs. The attempt to tag the top plug was unsuccessful. We are requesting approval to pull the cement stinger out of the hole and then trip in the hole with the 11-3/4" EZSV. We will then set the EZSV per the planned depth and attempt to pressure test below the EZSV to the approved test pressure of 2;000 psi. If the test is successful; we will proceed per the previously approved plan. If the test is unsuccessful; we will squeeze cement into the casing below the EZSV (approximately 42 bbls casing volume) to effectively isolate the casing shoe from the hole below.  At this point; we will proceed with the approved TA procedure.
Please let me know if you need additional information for review.  The previously approved procedure and schematic is attached.

Thurs 2.2 - POOH with FasDrill Running Tool. Slip and Cut drill line. RIH with lock down sleeve and land same. Monitor for no flow for 30 minutes - Good Test.

Fri 2.3 - Spot surface cement plug - 130cuft 15.6ppg Class A. POOH above plug and circulate. WOC. Cement in place @ 13:45. (Cement Plug spotted F/10;890' MD/TVD T/10;607' MD/TVD). Displace well @ 10;890' F/ 13.5 ppg SOBM (13.7 DHE) T/ 8.6 ppg sea water monitoring bbl in/bbl out.

Perform FIT-Perform FIT at 10.125" shoe set at 28;420 ft MD / 25;376 ft TVD with 13.6 ppg surface MW SBM (13.88 ppg static downhole MW). Tue 7.18 - POOH with 8-1/2" Cleanout Assembly. Circulate slug to surface and begin POOH wet . Begin pumping out of hole T/21;322' due to swabbing. Spot 16.2 ppg slug and POOH F/21;322' T/2;500' 

Wed 7.19 - POOH with 8-1/2" Cleanout BHA. Slip and cut drill line. Perform planned maintenance. P/U 8-1/2" Drilling assembly and RIH with same. Wash down F/28;407' T/28;510'. Drill 8-1/2" section F/28;510' T/28;535'.

Thurs 7.20 - Drill 8-1/2" section F/25;535' T/28;785' MD. Encounter tar and experience stuck pipe issues. Work pipe free and observe losses. Wash and ream up T/28;563'. Flow check on TT with a 9 bbl/hr gain rate. Close upper annular and monitor pressures. Line up to circulate well via Driller's Method. Maintain 1;300 psi DPP during remaining circulation.

Fri 7.21 - Performed second circulation of Driller's Method. Displace riser to 13.8 ppg SBM. Sweep stack. Observed pressure on drill pipe side. Bled 3.2 bbl to trip tank. Open strip tank and lose 3 bbl and see increase DP pressure. Pump down DP and monitor pressures.

Sat 7.22 - Circulate 13.8 ppg SBM (13.95 DHE). Shut in well and monitor pressures. Observe same trends as previous shut in indicating U-tubing of heavy mud. Mon 7.24 - Finished circulating bottoms up at the shoe. Took SCR's. Flow checked well-static. Pumped out of hole T/16;938'. POOH wet 5 stands; pumped 70 bbls of 16.2 ppg SBM slug; followed by 12 bbls 13.8 ppg SBM (14.3 DHE). POOH speed restricted.

configuration and set as proposed.**

Thurs 8.3 - Continue to TIH with 7 5/8" liner on 5 7/8 DP to 6;550' MD. R/U OES Flow back tool. Continue to TIH with 7 5/8" liner on 6 5/8" DP to 28;400' MD. Obtained parameters and started to wash and ream. down to bottom.

Wed 8.9 - Reverse circulate bacse oil out of the well. Circulate B/U. RIH below the TOL and tagged @ 27;838' MD. Attempted to test top of liner (no success). Estabilish injectivity rates. Pump OOH.

Fri 8.11 - Continue to TIH with 10 1/8" Fasdril. Set Fasdrill at 27;825' MD. Attempted to perform second liner top squeeze w/365 cuft 15.6ppg cement- couldn't squeeze cement. Circulate cement out of the hole.

Mon 8.14 - TIH w/8.5'' clean out assy t/27;339'; Obtain parameters & SCR`s; Wash/Ream t/27;815'; Drill FasDrill @27;818'; Continue wash t/27;928' TOL (27;928' MD / 24;988' TD); Circulate B/U; POOH wet t/26;537'; Pump Slug; POOH rack back clean out assy; P/U 6 1/2'' Drliling assy

Wed 8.16 - Tag FasDrill at 29;623'. Attempt to perform pressure test on 7-5/8" liner to 1;600 psi- bad test. POOH T/25;259'. Circulate slug out of drillstring. Pump up ESD readings. Pump up Min ESD = 14.53; Max ESD = 15.05 ppg at 210 gpm / 3100 psi as per DD. 

Thurs 8.17 - Displace well to 13.8 ppg (14.0 DHE). Drill out FasDrill. P/U and circulate until ECD's decrease. Resume drilling float equipment; float shoe and 10 feet of new formation. Perform FIT with a resulting max ESD of 15 ppg. 1190psi surface pressure. Drill 6-1/2" section T/29;984'.

Mon 8.21 - Drill to TD at 30;717' MD and 27;172' TVD. Circulate hole clean. Log up and attempt FPWD.

Tue 8.22 - Wash down and attempt final pressures; abort tests due to unsuccessful pressure attempts. Pump out of hole to TOL. POOH wet to space out for BOPs. Begin BOP testing. Abort BOP test to P/U storm packer and get in position to set packer if weather escalates.

Thurs 8.24 - Wait on weather. Receive communication to resume operations. Pump out of hole to TOL. Pull out of hole wet and transfer packer assembly to Aux. R/U for BOP testing; test lines. Perform Test #3 online; perform Tests 1; 2; 14; and 15 offline.

Fri 8.25 - Perform BOP test rams to 300/ 6;500 psi for 5/5 minutes and annulars to 300/3;000 psi for 5/5 each with 13.8 ppg SBM (14.0 DHE). BOP function on 4-1/2" DP F/ DCP Blue pod. ; Diverter function; and test TIWs. TIH to 7-5/8" Shoe.

Tue 8.29 - Continue TIH with Lower Completion Assy.

R/U & prepare to displace well from 14.0 ppg SBM to 14.0 ppg Brine.

Thurs 8.31 - Displace Choke ; Kill & Boost to brine. Conduct Pre-Displacement meeting. Displace well from 14.0 ppg SBM to 14.0 ppg Brine. Clean trip tank #1; wash strip tank; shakers; process pits; ditch; flush hole fill lines; install HPDU flanges

Fri 9.1 - completed cleaning; Installed and tested HPDU flanges; Performed BOP and Diverter Function test F/ DCP yellow pod; and F/ TCP blue pod. Circulated clean 14.0 ppg clean brine around (solids .025; NTU's 71). R/U Frac head; connect Frac lines to boat. Load ball launcher.

Sat 9.2 - R/U Frac equipment; Tested all surface lines to 14;300 psi w/14.0 ppg (14.0 DHE) CaBr2-good tests.; established reverse circulation rates; test frac lines to boat to 14;300 psi; Perform frac job as per procedure"},{"   ":65,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608124011200,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-09-03","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 9.3 - Continue pumping fac job as per procedure on stages 2-6. Mon 9.4 - R/D Frac hose and lay out; R/D Frac head assy and lay out same; R/D ball launcher equipment and chiksan iron; POOH & L/D tools; P/U intermediate string and RIH to 2;406

Tue 9.5 - RIH with intermediate string; Hold prejob meeting on shifting IB4 closed.

Wed 9.6 - Pressure up to 3;000 psi and release PO tool; Close FS2 valve. shear off ball seat with with 4;339 psi; Tested FS2 and PBR seal assembly to 2;000 psi-good tests; circulated bottoms up; POOH to 16;367'; Circulate slug out of hole while wait on blackhawk packer personnel

Thurs 9.7 - Waiting on Weather; RIH on 5 7/8" drill pipe F/ 16;460' T/ 21;107'' speed restricted at 1.5 min/stand; Picked up and made up test assembly; testing BOPs on 4 1/2" drill pipe F/ DCP Blue pod A using 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Rams to 300/6400 for 5/5; annulars to 300/2900 for 5/5 - good tests. Started Function Test of BOPs F/DCP blue & TCP yellow.

Fri 9.8 - RIH with 10 3/4 storm packer; unable to get packer through wellhead; POOH with 10 3/4'' packer and L/D same; POOH to 11;976'; slip 155' of drill line; RIH to 13;575'; P/U backup 10 3/4'' storm packer & RIH to 16;130

Mon 9.11 - Rig up for running upper completion; Offload IWOCS reel from boat and spot into position; Run upper completion; P/U chemical injection assy and terminate control line

Tue 9.12 - Terminate control line to CIM. Pressure test CIM to 15;000 psi for 15 minutes. RIH T/950' and terminate TEC line to PDHPG. Perform good pressure test on TEC to 30;000 psi for 15 minutes. RIH on 4-1/2" Tubing F/950' T/14;954'.

Wed 9.13 - P/U SCSSV. Terminated control line; functioned SCSSV; and pressure tested Control lines. Ran remaining tubing. P/U Tubing hanger; and M/U same. Terminated control lines and test. R/U; P/U THRA and land and lock same to Tubing Hanger.

Thurs 9.14 - Land and lock THRA onto Tubing Hanger. Perform seal integrity test to 7;000 psi. Terminate dual line flatpack and pressure test SV1 and SV2. TIH with upper completion on 6-5/8" landing string. Land TH with 20k; take overpull and maintain 30k tension. Pressure test TH seals; SV1/SV2 to 12;000 psi for 15 minutes. (good test).; and surface lines.

Fri 9.15 - Test Tubing hanger seals to 13;100 psi for 15 minutes. (Good Test); then under SCSSV to 500 psi for 15 minutes (Good Test) Re-apply control line pressure to 11;000 psi and open the SCSSV. Spot packer fluid. Set production packer at 27;133' MD 24;368' TVD. Perform 5;000 psi negative test on production packer for 15 min (good test). Perform 2;750 psi negative test on SCSSV-good test. Open SCSSV. perform 3;600 psi positive test on production packer for 30 min-good test. Cement unit test AAV to 2;000 psi for 15 minutes-good test. Close SCSSV; bleed off psi above SCSSV to 0 psi; bled back 1 bbl. Monitor no flow for 5 minutes. (Good Test)  Unlatch THRA from tubing hanger. L/D land-out assembly. Begin displacing landing string and c/k/b lines to seawater.

Sat 9.16 - Finish seawater displacement. POOH with landing string and THRA. Mitigate dropped damaged clamp. Resume POOH with landing string and THRA. R/D completion running equipment and sheaves. Begin R/U to pull riser. "},{"   ":67,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608124011200,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-09-17","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 9.17 - P/U Diverter running tool and M/U same. Pull diverter. ROV performs tree functions and testing. Set cap on tree. Pressure test BX gasket on Tree T/ 13;500psi. Hold pressure test for 15min - good test.

Mon 9.18 - Pull subsea BOP on riser. ***JOB COMPLETE***"},{"   ":68,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608124011200,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-12-05","TEXT_REMARK":"Tue 12.5 - Move rig to Stones 6R Safe Zone. ROV place beacons and bridge establish DP. R/U riser DP to spaceout OWIRs. Perform dummy run and space out. Pick up flowhead and surface tree. FMC function OWIRs valves and perform pressure test on riser Cement pressure test with seawater to 300 psi low and 8;300 psi high for 5 min. each test. Good Test. P/U CT BOP.

Wed 12.6 - Finish R/U surface equipment. Function CT BOP and perform accumulator drawdown. Perform coil tubing surface pressure tests to 300 psi low for 5 min. 11;500 psi high for 10 min-good tests. Suspend CT BOP testing to latch OWIRS due to upcoming weather front. Attempt to test VX gasket - Bad test. Resume CT BOP testing while ROV recovers to surface to obtain new gasket.

Thurs 12.7 - Perform OWIRS tests # 1; 8; 9. Perform Surface CT BOP tests 6; 5 and 1. WOW and decide to proceed with remaining OWIRS tests 2-7.

Fri 12.8 - Wait on weather. ROV test TST VX gasket to 8;500 psi for 30 minutes with RAIV and RXOV closed- good test. Continued to wait on weather to perform final OWIRS wet verification tests.

Sat 12.9 - WOW. Perform deadman and autoshear test on OWIRS. Restest VX gasket. Perform test #7 on CT BOP. Align surface iron and perform displacement to 12.5 ppg brine."},{"   ":69,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608124011200,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-12-10","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 12.10 - M/U CT BHA and RIH obtaining P/U and S/O at 27;772'. Mon 12.11 - Coil Tubing Parted. Mobilize equipment for plan forward and wait on kill weight brine to be shipped to location. Cut back heavy brine and spike fluid to 14.1 ppg.

MMS Correspondence:
* E-mail Marshall/McCarroll on 08/15/06 at 7:45 am as follows:
I spoke with Bryan Sunday morning regarding our temporary abandonment of the Stones #2 well in WR 508.  We recovered the compatts and set the 100' surface cmt plug as per the plan when the ROV got hung up around 8;000' and incurred winch problems.  We were granted approval to come back with another boat to set the TA cap; recover the ADCP; and to complete the bottom site survey.

I promised to provide you with our anticipated date of arrival back on location to complete the work: 
The only ROV equipped vessel we have on contract capable of working at this water depth is the AHV Ross Chouest.  The Ross is currently prepping the GC 599 site for the arrival of the Nautilus next week.  This creates an ETA to Stones for approximately August 27th; 2006.  Limitations with the Ross Chouest to launch the ROV require loop currents less than 2 knots.  We will continue to monitor the currents at Stones.  Based on the operational window of the Nautilus move and the loop currents at the Stones location; we will complete the TA requirements in the first available window of opportunity.

Once the work is completed; then I will provide you with a summary of this remaining work.  In the meantime; I have completed the TA program summary and wellbore sketch that Randy Allen will be submitting to you later. 
* E-mail McCarroll/Marshall on 08/15/06 at 7:46 am acknowledging update. 
* RMN on 08/11/06. 
* E-mail Marshall/McCarroll on 08/21/06 at 7:28 am as follows:
Apparently loop currents are affecting the pace of work at Friesian which in turn affects us at Stones.  The latest estimate to get an AHV to WR 508 is 31 August.
Will continue to keep you posted.
* E-mail McCarroll/Marshall on 08/22/06 at 7:47 am acknowledging update.

MMS Correspondence: 
*Verbal/e-mail correspondence McWilliams/Coco on 11/12/08 as follows:
Shell WR 508 #3 BP02 OCSG 17001- Extension of BOP pressure test on 4.1/2" DP
Mr Coco; 
With reference to our recent conversation on the above subject. 
Background 
The Schlumberger MDT tool is currently in the hole on a mixed drill pipe string.  We have been successful in acquiring pressures and samples and are currently about half way through the sampling program. The 14 day BOP test is due today and Schlumberger and Shell have concerns that if we pull out to test the BOP on 4.1/2" drill pipe then run back to continue the sampling program the samples may be at risk to seal failure due to cycling the external pressure on the tool.

Proposal 
Our proposal is to pull the MDT tool inside the 9.3/8" shoe; test the BOP on 6.5/8" drill pipe along with the auxilliary valves and surface equipment to meet the 14 day test requirement.  Then test the BOP on 4.1/2" drill pipe on the way out of the hole with the MDT string which we anticipate to be on approximately November 15th.   Our reasoning here is that we have a good overbalance in the hole (<1;000psi) and that in the unlikely event of a well control issue during the MDT program we would be closing the BOP on 6.5/8" drill pipe.  The first time 4.1/2" drill pipe would be across the BOP would be when we retrieve the MDT string; at which point we are proposing to conduct the test.

Approval 
I understand that you have given verbal approval to extend the BOP test on 4.1/2" drill pipe only; by 48 hours; to 2:30 PM on Friday November 14th.   Prior to this time I will contact you and provide an update on the sampling program and a refined time on when we would expect to conduct the pressure test.

As per your request; we will note you verbal approval of the above on the IADC report. 
Grateful if you would confirm above by e-mail return. 

*11/12/08 e-mail reply Coco/McWilliam as follows: Confirmed.
*11/14/08 e-mail McWilliam/Coco as follows: Reference our conversation; the rig has completed the current sampling program and preparing to pull out. This would mean testing the rams on 4.5" pipe tomorrow Sat November 15th.
*11/14/08 e-mail Coco/McWilliam as follows: Extension granted until 11/15/2008.

MMS Correspondence: 
*e-mail correspondence McWilliam/Coco on 11/21/08 as follows:
McWilliam/Coco:
Mr Coco; This is an email follow-up to the voice message I left on your mobile number. 
Background
We have cemented our 7.5/8" liner in place and achieved good pressure tests on both the ZXP packer and the liner.  We have commenced the TA operations as per the approved program; displaced the well to 16.4 ppg riser margin mud from the top of the 7.5/8" liner hanger to 19;200' and are about to commence.   
 
Plan
The planned operation is to continue as per TA program and set a cement retainer and a second cement plug which we anticipate to be tomorrow afternoon (Sat Nov 22nd)
 
Request
Our 30 day shear ram test is due tomorrow Sat Nov 22nd.  Given that we are now working in cased hole with tested liner and considerable overbalance (>1;000 psi) at reservoir depth; and in the process of executing out TA program; our request is to MMS is to waive the test on the shear rams
Grateful if you could confirm if this is acceptable.

Coco/McWilliam:
Verbal approval granted.  Note this approval in the IADC report on the rig and WAR to be submitted for this week¿s activity.

*e-mail correspondence McWilliam/Coco on 11/22/08 as follows:
McWilliam/Coco:
Mr Coco; Thank you for the approval for the request as outlined below.
 
Since the time of the request and approval; we have pulled out with the liner running tool and found that 18' of the tool has been left down hole.  We will therefore not be able to immediately proceed with the remainder of the TA program as I had previously outlined; but will first have to recover the running tool.
 
The barriers that I stated in the previous request i.e. the tested liner; packer and overbalance remain in place.  As such we feel comfortable proceeding with the operation without a new shear ram pressure test.  However; as this recovery operation was not explicitly stated in my previous waiver request (as we did not know at that time) I would seek you approval to extend the waiver to cover the recovery operations for retrieving the running tool.

McWilliam/Coco:
Mr Coco;
As per our telephone conversation at 12:15 PM on November 22nd; 2009;  thank you for your verbal approval of our request as outlined below.

Attempt to release running tool from assembly; troubleshoot."},{"   ":254,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-10-09","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 10.9 - SB3 packer is set at 24;934'MD / 24;414'TVD. Troubleshoot release of SC-XP running tool from SB-3 packer. Rotate to release - successful. Pressure test IB-4 / SB-3 to 2;500 psi for 15 min- good test. POOH to surface. P/U and RIH w/ Frac Seal assembly.

Mon 10.10 - RIH w/ Frac Seal Assembly F/ 9;640' T/ 24;896' MD. Stab seals; open IB-4; and shoulder out on centralizer sub. Locate top of centralizer sub at 24;896' MD. Mark Bullhead position. P/U to Reverse. Circulate bottoms up. Begin displacement to brine.

Tue 10.11 - Displaced well to 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Clean surface lines and circulate/filter well. Begin R/U for frac.

Wed 10.12 - RU for frac job; test lines.

Thurs 10.13 - Completed testing surface lines. Obtained injection rates. Staged solvent and pumped mini frac. Pumped stage 1 frac.

Fri 10.14 - Troubleshoot frac sleeves. Replace leaking valves on surface frac iron and re-test. Attempt to inject/shift frac sleeves.

Sat 10.15 - Cycled pressure on tubing; monitoring bbl in/out. Stripped up to reverse port. Attempted to reverse out up work string. Bled down tubing pressure and monitored pressure response."},{"   ":255,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-10-16","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 10.16 - Establish communication from annulus to DP. Reverse out gelled fluid from tubing with 14 ppg CaBr. Strip to bullhead position.

Mon 10.17 - Attempt to inject into formation. Cycle pressure F/5;000 T/1;500 psi - No Success. Mobilize contingency wireline equipment.

Tue 10.18 - Continue cycling pressure F/5;000 T/1;500 psi to establish injection - No success. Prep to Pressure and Function Test BOPs. Function Test Diverter. Test BOP F/TCP blue pod on 6 5/8" profile with 14.0 ppg brine; annular & associated fail safes valves T/300 psi low for 5 min; and 2;800 psi high for 5 min.

Wed 10.19 - Complete BOP testing F/TCP blue pod on 6 5/8" profile with 14.0 ppg
brine; T/300 psi low for 5 min; and 6;600 psi high for 5 min. Cycle tubing pressure F/1;500 T/5;000 psi and F/1;500 T/8;000 psi to attempt to establish injection - no success. Inflow test frac head valves. R/D Coflex and upper frac head for wireline.

Thurs 10.20 - R/U Powerwire; bails and elevators. R/U concentric flange adapter. Configure and test wireline BOP shear/seal ram with sub sea test unit to 300 psi. low for 5 min & 10k psi high (RWP) for 5 min. and R/U same.

Fri 10.21 - TIH CCL/GR Wireline BHA. Tag bottom at 27;882' MD / 27;055' TVD. POOH. M/U Tubing Punch BHA.

Sat 10.22 - M/U Perforating BHA and Lubricator and Pressure test lubricator quick test sub with sub sea test unit w/ water T/ 300 psi low F/5 min & 9;400 psi high F/5 min. RIH. Attempt to power up tools below mudline; no success. POOH. Identified missing BHA. Call out contingency equipment.
"},{"   ":256,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-10-23","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 10.23 - Wait on Equipment. M/U 2.125" Blind Box BHA and RIH same. Tagged fish at 27;872' MD 27;022' TVD.. POOH.

Mon 10.24 - POOH Blind Box BHA. M/U perforating BHA and RIH on eline. POOH perf. BHA due to tool failure. M/U spare perf. BHA and RIH. **Nelson - Shell may proceed with proposed perforation as requested.(roughly ~27;845ft MD)**

Tue 10.25 - Perforate tubing (Perforations from 27;848' MD 27;025' TVD to 27;845 MD 27;046' TVD). POOH perf BHA on e-line. R/D wireline equipment. Begin R/U of frac head and frac hose.

Wed 10.26 - Finish rig up and prep for frac. Begin Frac job at treatment 4.

Thurs 10.27 - Continue treatment 5 of frac job through end of job (treatment 12). P/U to reverse position. Continue P/U to attempt closure of IB-4. Troubleshoot closure.

Fri 10.28 - Closed IB-4. Reversed out work string. Pressure test IB-4 / SB-3 with cmt unit with 14.0 ppg brine T/250/3;000 psi 5/5 minutes. R/D Frac Equipment. Reverse out another work string volume. Benchmark and begin SureTec BOP testing to 250/6600 Low/High for 5 min. each with 14.00 ppg Brine. Test Annular F/DCP yellow pod on 5 7/8" profile with 14.0 ppg brine T/300 psi low for 5 min; and 2;800 psi high for 5 min.

Sat 10.29 - Finish BOP testing on 5-7/8" to 250/6600 Low/High for 5 min. each with 14.00 ppg Brine. POOH wet w/ IB-4 shifter and frac seal assembly. Perform Maintenance at surface. RIH w/ BSRTT. **Nelson - 14day casing test extension granted**"},{"   ":257,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-10-30","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 10.30 - RIH w/ BSRTT. Set BSRTT and test BSRs with 14.0 CaBa2 T/ 300/6;600 psi for 5/5
minutes. Slip and Cut Drill Line while testing. POOH w/ BSRTT. P/U and RIH w/ Intermediate Completion. **Nelson - Approval granted to proceed with permitted completion operations**

Mon 10.31 - RIH w/ intermediate completion. Test Annular on 4-1/2" DP with 14.0 ppg brine; T/300 psi low for 5 min; and 2;800 psi high for 5 min. F/TCP blue pod. Test Rams on 4-1/2" DP with 14.0 ppg brine; T/300 psi low for 5 min; and 6;600 psi high for 5 min. Continue RIH w/ intermediate completion F/TCP blue pod. RIH with intermediate completion & clean well equipment on 6 5/8" DP. Latch into wear bushing @ 21;167 MD 21;028 TVD (9;630 tool depth); confirm latch with 10k overpull. *Ledet - Shell may proceed with running the intermediate completion with the two stands of 4-1/2" drill pipe.**

Tue 11.1 -  Open IB-4 valve. Latch seal anchor into PBR. Release PO tool. Close FS-2 valve. POOH with clean well equipment and jet THS.

Wed 11.2 - POOH with intermediate completion running tool and clean well tools. R/U tubing running equipment.

Thurs 11.3 - RIH w/ upper completion. M/U LSOTJ; XN Nipple; production packer; CIM; PDPG

Fri 11.4 - RIH w/ upper completions F/ 6;025' T/ 12;109'; M/U SCSSV; RIH F/12;160' T/15;177'; M/U TH. R/D tubing running equipment.

Sat 11.5 - Terminated and tested control lines on tubing hanger. PU THRA and locked THRA to tubing hanger. Tested THRA. RIH w/ tubing hanger and THRA."},{"   ":258,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-11-06","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 11.6 - Finish RIH w/ Upper Completion. Latch into PBR. Collapse LSOTJ. Land; lock; and test Tubing Hanger.**FMC applied 5;000 psi to HST line block in pressure and hold for 5 minutes (14.0 CaBr) to confirm TH fully landed; good test. Continued slacking off and set down all production string weight plus 30k (260k).** Reverse circulate in packer fluid.**Spot 12.0 packer fluid in annulus with rig pumps as per Halliburton procedure.** Set Production Packer.Test SCSSV Test SCSSV from reverse position T/ 1000 psi F/ 15 mins see chart.; set production packer @
3;000psi. Continue pressuring up work string after packer set as per prog. Hold 4;000 psi F/15 mins.** Perform negative pressure test on production packer F/15 min straight line (see chart).  21060 - {12 x 23;428 x .052 + 1250] = 5191 differential test(top of packer at 24;280' MD); and pressure up on back side from 1;000 psi to 2;000 psi and test AAV and charted for 15 minutes.

Mon 11.7 - Unlatched THRT. Displaced choke/kill/boost line; landing string; and riser to seawater. POOH w/ landing string.

Tue 11.8 - L/D Spanner. Slip and cut drill line. Prepare decks for pulling riser. Rig up to pull riser. Pull Diverter. P/U Landing joint.

Wed 11.9 - Unlatch BOP. Move Rig to safe zone. Overboard X-Tree. Pull riser. Install and test X-Tree.

Thurs 11.10 - **ROV continued installing well 10 subsea tree and perform connector
and gallery testing to 13;100psi per APM.** ROV completed X-Tree installation. **Job Complete**"},{"   ":259,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-11-20","TEXT_REMARK":"Mon 11.20 - Space out DP riser. R/U crossover and surface flow tree. Function test and perform integrity test. Pressure test CT/CTC. Change out KA1 valve and continue CT BOP stump testing. R/U CT BOP and hydraconn.

Tue 11.21 - Continue to R/U surface lines and FMC SFT. R/U control lines to CT BOPs. Functioned test CT BOPs. Performed accumulator drawdown test. Performed CT BOP pressure test to 300 psi and 9;300 psi for 5 min each-good test. R/U WL valves; functioned test same and performed accumulator drawdown test. WOW.

Wed 11.22 - Continue to WOW. P/U WL lubricator and test same to 300 psi and 9;300 psi for 5 min each-good tests. Install night cap and needle valve. Flushed 2 3/8" annulus tubing with 8.6 ppg SW. Move rig to well center and flush production riser with 8.6 ppg SW. Landed and latch OWIRS on SST. FMC performed inital latch up tests. Performed OWIRS on bottom tests to 300 psi and 9;300 psi for 5 min each-good tests.

Thurs 11.23 - Continue to perform OWIRS wet verification. Displaced surface lines and riser to 12.5 ppg brine. R/U SL BHA and PCE. Test same to 300 psi and 9;300 psi for 5 min each-good tests. FMC and ROV open XT and attempt to bullhead. Bled off pressure on Expro choke. RIH with SL to 23;052 SLM. Tagged 5 times. POOH and L/D BHA and SL PCE. F/T CT BOPs and RIH with CT milling BHA.

Fri 11.24 - Continue to RIH with CT milling BHA to 22;852' breaking circulation every 1;000 ft and Expro maintaining BH @ 18;100-18;400 psi. Circulate bottoms up. @ 1.3 bpm. HES CT work pipe F/ 22;852' CTM T/ 22;800' CTM during circulation. Stage pumps down while Expro maintain BHP @ 18;400 psi - 18;200 psi. Shut in well on choke and RIH from 22;800' to 25;958' @ 25 fpm. Tagged 2k down @ 25;958'. Washed down with 12.5 ppg brine @ 1 bpm from 25;958' to 26;005'. Circulate BU at 1.3 bpm maintain Expro choke maintain BHP- 18;100 psi- 18;200 psi.

Sat 11.25 - Circulated B/U @ 26;000 ft. RIH and wash down to 27;200 ft. Circulate B/U. Drained and clean MGS to shaker house lines. POOH from 27;200 ft to 23;671 ft while pumping @ 0.25 bpm. Flushed MGS and surface lines. Continue to circulate and lost returns. Shut in and clean MSG and surface lines. Resumed circulation until lost of returns. Shut in and flushed MSG cleaning proppant. Continue to circulate. HES pump failed on the fluid end. Lined up cement unit to CT string and continue to circulate. RIH to 24;700 ft."},{"   ":260,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-11-26","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 11.26 - Continue to circulate @ 0.5bpm. Washed down F/27046' CTM T/27;236' CTM. Pumped 5bbls of sweep and circualted B/U. S/D pump and cleaned and flushed MGS. TIH F/26;929' CTM; and tag at 27;165' with 4k down. Washed down T/27;315' CTM. Pumped 5bbls of sweep and circualted B/U. P/U T/27;285' CTM. Washed/Milled T/27;471 CTM; tagged hard at this depth. Flagged CT and P/U 30ft. RIH t/ 27;468' CTM tagged with 2 k down. P/U to 27;000 ft CTM and Circulate B/U.

Mon 11.27 - Continue to mill through lower completion sleeves. Pump sweeps and circulate B/U as needed. Shut down pumps and shut in well to clean and flush MGS and shaker house lines.Milled down to top sleeve of stage 5 @ 27;744' CTM.

Tue 11.28 - Milled seats of stage 5. TIH w/ CT and tagged top seat of stage 4 @ 27;785' CTM. Pumped gel sweeps while POOH to 27;130 CTM and circulated B/U.TIH w/ pumps to 27;773' CTM and tagged w/ 2k down. Circulated B/U while POOH to 8;000' CTM. Closed OWIRS and continued to POOH to 2;000' CTM.

Wed 11.29 - Continue to R/U WL PCE and dummy assembly. PT and FT same. RIH and tagged @ 27;791' MD. POOH to 27;000' MD and logged back down and tagged again @ 27;791' MD. POOH to above OWIRS and close RPIV and PRV valves. Continue to POOH to surface.
B/O lubricator and L/D dummy assembly.

Thurs 11.30 - L/D dummy bailer assembly and P/U cement bailer.Function test same and filled with cement. M/U assembly into lubricator and RIH with bailer assembly while quick testing PCE. Dump cement (7.1 gal. of 17 ppg CMT.) @ 27;785' MD. POO; reconfigured cement bailer; mix and filled with cement. P/U and M/U bailer assembly #2 into lubricator. RIH while quick testing PCE. Tagged @ 27;783' MD. Dump cement (7.1 gal. of 17 ppg CMT.) and POOH.

Fri 12.1 - POOH w/ E-Line to surface. R/D E-Line and R/U CT wash BHA and injector head. RIH w/ CT to 9;569' CTM; wash across OWIRS and XT at 1.5 bpm. Continue to RIH to 26;000' CTM.

Sat 12.2 - Continue to RIH to 27;772' CTM and tagged w/ 2k down. Start circualting gel sweeps and chasing w/ brine. Circulate B/U. Line up CT pump on acid tanks and perform acid wash job. Wait +/- 6 hrs.Bullhead acid. POOH while pumping."},{"   ":261,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-12-03","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 12.3 - Continue to POOH w/ CT to surface. R/D CT acid wash BHA and skid injector head off WC. Displace surface lines and riser to seawater. R/D temporary iron. Unlock and unlatch OWIRS package from Stones 10. Move rig to safe zone. R/D CT BOP. ROV prepare to install tree cap.

Mon 12.4 - Continue to R/D surface equipment. Change bails from 750 ton to 500 ton and P/U manual elevator for 5 7/8" DP. L/D top joint. POOH until annulus gooseneck and valves are above rig floor. Waited on ROV to pick up beacons and install and test tree cap. XT cap installed; pressure test complete 13.1 ksi for 5 min; test good. Begin move to 6R. End of Report."},{"   ":262,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2019-06-14","TEXT_REMARK":"06/14/2019:  Received verbal from Mr. Bill Sanders to remove tree (see attached).  Stump tested OWIRs.  

06/15/2019:  Continued displacing OWIRS to drill water.  Tested EXOV and RXOV with soap. Good test. Began displacing OWIRS cavity to 8.3 ppg drill water. P/U 33 stands of 5-7/8" XTM riser."},{"   ":263,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2019-06-16","TEXT_REMARK":"6/16/2019: Completed OWIRs testing.  Performed deadman and Autoshear simulation.

6/17/2019:  Skid OWIRS to well center. M/U speedlock and annulus flange to EDP. Pressure tested connection. Unlocked package from test stump and transferred to inspection stand. Finished pre-deployment checklist. Splashed OWIRS and RIH on 5-7/8" XTM-57 riser to ~3;200 ft.

6/18/2019:  RIH on 5-7/8" XTM-57 riser ~9;600 ft. Moved to well center and performed dummy spaceout. Added spaceout pups. Pressure tested 5-7/8" riser and 2-3/8" annulus pipe to 9;500 psi for 5 min on chart with Halliburton cement unit. Good test.

6/19/2019:  R/U CCTLF. M/U FMC surface tree. M/U speed lock. M/U surface iron on rig floor.

6/20/2019:  Stab CT into injector head and install injector head onto CCTLF porch. Cont. R/U surface iron. Test CT BOPs and surface equipment to 300 psi/9;500 psi. Leak detected between FMC surface tree and string. R/D CT equipment.  (Received verbal from Bobby Nelson to proceed with operations while RPM for WCV/Shear doc is in review by district - see attached.)

6/21/2019:  Continued R/D CT equipment due to leak between FMC surface tree and string. Replaced upper X/O. Tested 300 psi/9;500 psi. Recorded test on circle chart for 5 min. Test good.  Performed spaceout.

6/22/2019:  R/U CT BOP's. R/U Hydrocon. Install CT injector head. Tested CT BOP's 250-350 psi low and 9;500 psi high for 5 min each on the EZ chart.
"},{"   ":264,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2019-06-23","TEXT_REMARK":"6/23/2019:  Moved rig to safe zone. Landed OWIRS on SSXT. Latched up.
