Displaced riser with 13.0 ppg brine.  

6/24/2019:  Finished displacing riser with 13.0 ppg. Bullheaded well. RIH w/ Ct cement squeeze BHA.

6/25/2019:  Pump Cement Squeeze with 12.4 bbls of 16.2 ppg Class H cement (70 cuft).  Plug at 26;725' - 27;609' MD/____________TVD.  TOC = 26;725'.  Monitored squeeze for 30 min.  POOH to surface. Break Hydracon connection. Skid CT injector head. L/D cement squeeze BHA. R/U E-line BOP's. P/U 2.80" gauge. Pressure test lubricator. Tested cement plug to 1;500 psi for 15 min.; good test. 

6/26/2019:  RIH with E-Line and Log @ 24;340' to 24;100'. POOH and R/U Bridge Plug to E-Line. RIH with Bridge Plug on E-Line. Set Bridge Plug at 24;298'.  POOH.

6/27/2019:  Perforate Tubing at 24;250'; POOH w/ Perforating Tools on E-line. Displaced annulus to 13.0 ppg Brine. R/U Cement BHA to Coil Tubing; began RIH.

6/28/2019: Pump 400' Balanced Cement Plug with 146 cuft Class H cement. TOC = 23;850'.  POOH; Test plug to 1;000 PSI. Lower Coil Tubing Injector Head out of CCTLF; R/U Well Tech Tubing Cutter.

6/29/2019: RIH w/Tubing Cutter BHA. Cut 4-1/2inch 18.9 lb. Tubing @ 23;008' MD. POOH; Flush Jumper; Displace Riser to SW.
"},{"   ":265,"WELL_NAME":"SN110","API12":608124011001,"WAR_START_DT":"2019-06-30","TEXT_REMARK":"6/30/2019:  Unlock OWIRS f/XT; P/U OWIRS f/XT. Unlock XT f/THS.

7/1/2019: P/U XT; Move to Safe Zone; R/D CCTLF

7/2/2019: POOH w/ 5-7/8 XTM-57 OWIRS Riser.

7/3/2019: RIH w/THRT; Displace landing String to 13# brine.  Lock THRT to TH as per FMC procedure; POOH w/ 4 1/2" Tubing.

7/4/2019: Flushed CID Line; L/D THRT; L/D TH; R/U 4 1/2" handling equipment.  POOH w/ 4 1/2" Production Tubing; P/U Cement Head.

7/5/2019:  Pump 250ft balanced surface plug with 118 cuft of 15.8 ppg Lafarge Class A cement.  Plug depth 10;400' - 10;650' MD.  L/D Cement head; Move Rig to Safe Zone; POOH 4-1/2" Production Tubing; L/O 4-1/2" Production Tubing.  


7/6/2019: L/O 4-1/2" Production Tubing; P/U 7 5/8" Drill Pipe Offline; ROV Recover Beacons Offline. Demob all remaining surface equipment.  Prepare to move rig to MC392.  Final report.
"},{"   ":266,"WELL_NAME":"SN207","API12":608124011700,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-04-02","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 4.2 - Jetted 36" and let soak. 36" shoe @ 9;882' MD/TVD. Reset load cell pins in main TD. Released DAT and drillahead to 11;250'MD/TVD. Circulate seawater; Sapp pill; and Hi-vis sweep followed by displacing system to 11.5 ppg Pad mud. Ran 28" casing on Aux floor; waited on correct centralizers; and L/D shoe joint and replaced with spare prior to commencing running casing.

Mon 4.3 - Continue to circulate sweep around 28x32.5" hole section. Pump string volume plus 1.5x annulus. Flow check(well static). Pull out of the hole to 9;857' (tight spots at 10;784'; 10;671'; 10;300'). Run in hole with 28" casing to 10;631'. Wash down to 10;806'. Pump out of hole with casing. Trip in hole to 9;700' with 28"x 32.5". Displace drill string with 11.5 ppg WBM. Trip in hole to 9;882'. Washing down at 10;343'.

Tue 4.4 - Wash down with 28" x 32.5" BHA T/11;250'. Jet wellhead before POOH. Position AUX over wellcenter and stab 28" casing in wellhead. Displace inner string and casing to 11.5 ppg WBM. Land 28" casing at 11;164'. Pump 2992 cuft 13.3ppg Lafarge Class A lead cement and 916 cuft 15.6ppg Lafarge Class A bbl tail cement. (Total cement 3908 cuft) Cmt in place @ 15:30. Land out profile @ 9;673' MD/ 9;673' TVD. 28'' Shoe @ 11;164' MD/ 11;163.83 TVD. ETOC @ 11;005'. Release running tool and POOH with inner string and landing string. Move main to wellcenter and begin RIH with 26" BHA.

Wed 4.5 - RIH with 26" BHA. Drillout shoetrack and continue drilling to 13;940' MD/13;940' TVD w/ 8.6ppg seawater. Run 22" casing on AUX.

Thurs 4.6 - Finish drilling to TD at 14;544' MD 14;543' TVD. Circulate two bottoms up and flow check. POOH T/ 9;672' observing multiple tight spots. Inspect bit and Power drive. RIH to perform fast pass. Wash and ream T/13;180' MD at 600 ft/hr.

Fri 4.7 - POOH with 26" BHA. Displace 8.6 ppg seawater from landing string and inner string plus 50% with 13.0 ppg WBM. Run 22" Casing on 6 5/8" landing string F/ 11;164'MD; T/ 14;503'MD in 26" Open hole; fill up pipe every 15 stds W/ 13.0 WBM. Land out casing in 36" without landing RLSA. Begin cement job.

Sat 4.8 - Complete cement job with 6209 cuft. (2728cuft @ 13.3; 2942cuft 13.3ppg; 539cuft 15.6ppg); Lafarge Class A cement. Green Dye showed at sea floor. Displace w 8.6 seawater. Cement was in place at 02:00. ETOC inside shoetrack is 14;423'. Shoe @ 14;503' MD - 14;502' TVD. RIH with 36" Casing Cleanout Assembly and wash profile. POOH with same. Redress FMC RLSA and RIH and set seal. R/U and begin running BOP on riser."},{"   ":267,"WELL_NAME":"SN207","API12":608124011700,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-04-09","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 4.9 - Splashed BOP and began running BOP on riser. Shut down for dropped MUX clamp then resumed operations. Pressure tested rigid conduit; boost lines; choke/kill lines at 3;959'.

Mon 4.10 - Run Riser and specialty joints while testing rigid conduit; boost; choke; and kill lines every 12 hours.

Tue 4.11 - Install gooseneck hoses and latch BOP on HPWHH. Pressure test casing to against the lower BS ram to 4;500 psi for 30 min with 8.6ppg SW. Install diverter.

Wed 4.12 - Finished Rig Maintenance. Troubleshoot flow meter on Blue Pod. R/U diverter running tool and remove diverter. R/U riser pulling equipment; removed storm loops and MUX line. Pull gooseneck & hangoff. Start to pull riser.

Thurs 4.13 - Continue to pull riser and BOP to surface. Troubleshooting leak and change out hoses on the BOP.

Fri 4.14 - Functioned test BOPs and performed soak test. Transported BOPs to well center and splashed it at 1605 and started to run riser.

Sat 4.5 - Continue to run riser and BOPs. Test riser."},{"   ":268,"WELL_NAME":"SN207","API12":608124011700,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-04-16","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 4.16 - Installed hoses on the termination joint and test same. Performed dummy latch up and latched BOPs; performed overpull and slump test. TIH with FMC test plug assembly.

Mon 4.17 - SLB & subsea test upper shear rams; Connector; 2= 6 5/8 TIW; with
8.6 ppg sw to 300/8;300 psi for 5/5 min as per subsea test procedure; see EZ chart with ROV making functions (autoshear; deadman). Monitor riser on trip tank (static). 
Pressure test BOP with 8.6 ppg sw to 300/8;500 psi for 5/5 min; Test upper annular; lower annular and all associated valves 300/5;500 psi 5/5 minutes each and function test BOPs F/ DCP blue; TCP yellow; SCP yellow. Function diverter on 6-5/8" pipe from DCP. RIH with 16.5: BHA.

Tue 4.18 - Continue to RIH with 16.5" drilling BHA. Set wear bushing; displace well to 10.0 ppg SBM. Tag cement at 14;386' MD/TVD set 15K down. Drill out cement; floats; and 10' of new formation. Perform LOT. w/ SLB cmt unit w/10.0 ppg surface mud weight. (10.25 ppg downhole ESD mw) Observed highest pressure of 1;018 psi. Shoe depth 14;503 MD / TVD. Calculated EMW 11.60 ppg. 

Wed 4.19 - Drop 2" ball to activate reamer and cleanout shoe track. Drop 2.25" ball to deactivate reamer and drilled to 16;620 ft.

Thurs 4.20 - Drilling 16.5" hole section from 16;620 ft to 21;525 ft MD.

Fri 4.21 - Drill 16.5" hole section to TD @ 24;002' MD/ 22;477' TVD. Circulate 10.5 ppg SBM (10.8 DHE) viscous sweep and pumped 100 bbls of 12.5 ppg weighted sweep and circulate it out.

Sat 4.22 - Continue to circulate hole clean and POOH from 24002' to 14;443' MD with 16.5" BHA washing and working through multiple tight spots. Decided to RIH for a wiper trip."},{"   ":269,"WELL_NAME":"SN207","API12":608124011700,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-04-23","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 4.23 - Continue to RIH (wiper trip) with 16.5" BHA to TD @ 24;002' MD. Pump 200 bbls hi-vis sweep and weight up to 10.6 ppg SBM (10.8ppg DHEMW). Circulate hole clean. POOH from 24;002' to 18;315' MD at 3 min/stand.

Mon 4.24 - Continue to POOH. Wash 16" profile @ 14;014' MD/TVD. Space out and Function test BOP and Diverter. Pump a slug and continue to POOH to surface.L/D 16.5" BHA. R/U 13-5/8" Csg running equipment. RIH w/ 13-5/8" csg.

Tue 4.25 - TIH with stands of 13-5/8" Liner. P/U hanger and M/U same. R/U flowback tool and TIH with 13-5/8" casing on 6-5/8" 40# landing string. TIH on 6-5/8" 60# landing string.

return vol is 99%; 40 bbl loss. Cement in place at 15:30 with Est. TOC depth 21;621' MDft. Attempt to set seal assembly and pressure test same with no success. POOH with seal assembly.

Thurs 4.27 - POOH with 6-5/8" landing string with FMC Running Tool and Seal Assembly. Inspect seal assembly damage at surface and notice missing lock ring. Slip and cut drill line and perform rig maintenance. RIH with lock ring retrieval tool on 6-5/8" DP.

Fri 4.28 - TIH with Lock Ring Retrieval Assembly T/14;063'. Monitor well and observe 9-11 bbl/hr loss rate. POOH wet with Lock Ring Retrieval Assembly. TIH with Mill and Flush Assembly.

Thurs 5.4 - Perform 13-5/8" Casing Pressure Test to 4;500 psi w/10.65ppg SBM (10.8 DHE) f/30 minutes - good test. riser on trip tank (static). Open annular and pump up max ESD of 14.25 ppg. Surface MW: 11.0 ppg SBM (DHE 11.2ppg). Drill T/24;560'.

Fri 5.5 - Drill F/24;560' T/27;336'.

Sat 5.6 - TD'ed section at 27;825'MD/25;563'TVD. Begin pumping out of hole.

Sat 5.13 - Circulate B/U at the shoe. Flow check the well. Test BOPs to 300 low / 6600 high for 5 minutes each; test annular to 300 low / 3200 high for 5 min each. Mon 5.15 - L/D 12.25" x 14.75" Reamer BHA. R/U casing running equipment. Waited on boat to arrive on location with reamer shoe. M/U shoe and 10-1/8" pup jt. Run 10 1/8" singles. (good test) at TOL. Circulate DP volume. Pump 16.2ppg slug. POOH with running tool

Thurs 5.18 - Continue to POOH w/ hanger running tool. Slip and Cut. Function BSRs to clean cavities. P/U and RIH w/ BSR Test tool. POOH w/ FMC assembly to 5;100' MD

Close LVBR @ max pressure twice. Pump a slug
and POOH to surface. Tue 5.23 - Slip and Cut and pressure test casing to 6;200 psi w/ 13.6 ppg SBM for 30 minutes. Adjust LDB. P/U and RIH w/ FMC lock down bushing to set same. Test it to 7;500 psi. Release tool and POOH. P/U Brute packer; TIH to set same.

Wed 5.24 - Set Packer at 10;772' MD and pressure test same to 1;500 psi for 5 min. Perform negative test with 250 bbl of 6.6 ppg base oil for 30 minutes of no flow. Displace mud above packer to 8.6 ppg seawater. POOH with packer running tool.

Thurs 5.25 - Run BLAT and attempt to land out same. Pull BLAT and examine damage to antirotation keys. R/U and pull diverter and install landing joint. Unlatch BOP and move to safe zone. Land THS and perform open water testing. Land BOP on THS. Close lower BSR's & test connector to 1;000 psi F/ 5 min (good test). L/D landing joint and run diverter.

Fri 5.26 - Attempted to test BSR against Brute Packer with no success. Prepare BSRTT on aux and RIH with tail pipe T/522'. Function diverter. Function BSRTT on surface and consult whether internal sealing element sufficient. Decision to RIH was made. Perform BOP function test on 5-7/8" DP. Set BSRTT and attempt to perform BSR test #1 with no success. POOH with BSRTT.

Sat 5.27 - POOH BSRTT and redressed same. RIH with BSRTT and set in THS. Performed BSR and connector pressure tests to 300 / 8;800 psi. for 5 / 5 minutes each w/8.6 ppg (Good Tests). RIH and log F/24;500' T/ 24;642'. TIH T/26;500'. Log F/ 26;500' T/26;690'. Circulate bottoms up above wellhead and flowcheck.

Wed 5.31 - Perform Casing pressure test to 6;200 psi for 30 minutes-good test. Drill float collar; cement; and float shoe. Drill 10' of new formation. Calculated 15.33 max. Pumped in 9.6 bbls; bled back 9.6 bbls. Ream through rathole and drill T/28;002'.

Thurs 6.1 - Drill to 28;050' and attempt to activate reamer. Begin circulating while attempting to activate reamer. Decision made to drillahead with 8-1/2" bit. Drill F/28;050' T/28;587'.

Fri 6.2 - Drill F/28;587' T/29;869'.

Sat 6.3 - Drill to TD at 31;080' MD - 28;179' TVD. Pump weighted sweep and Hi-Vis sweep. Begin circulating sweeps out of hole.

"},{"   ":275,"WELL_NAME":"SN207","API12":608124011700,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-06-04","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 6.4 -Circulated out weighted sweep and Hi-Vis sweep with 13.8 ppg SBM (14.0 DHE). Mon 6.5 - Pump out of hole and take FPWD data at designated depths. Check stethoscope hole ID in casing. Pump out of hole and change saver sub to 5-7/8" at 23;738'. Troubleshoot PS-30s. Continue pumping out of hole T/ 13;463'.

Tue 6.6 - POOH w/ 8.5" BHA to surface. Removed radioactive sources as per SLB. Changed out elevator inserts and lay down BHA. Performed maintenance on Standpipe manifold; serviced block and serviced IBOPS on main TDX. P/U Cleanout BHA and RIH with same to above BOPs.

Wed 6.7 - Slip and Cut. Perform BSR function test. Continue to RIH w/ cleanout BHA to 23;500' MD scraper depth. Wash and ream from 23;500 to 23;780' MD scraper depth w/ 10-1/8" string mill and scraper across tieback; seal gap; and shoetrack. Pump 75 bbls of sweep and 120 bbls of Hi-vis sweep.

Thurs 6.8 - Circulate on bottom. Pump out of hole f/ 31;080' t/ 16;791' MD @ an average 2-1.5 min/std; 350 gpm and 2;600 psi SPP. Noticed 60k overpull @ 30;940' MD and @ 20k overpull @ 30;574' MD.

Fri 6.9 - Continue pumping out of hole f/ 16;791' t/ 13;861' MD. Changed out saver sub and elevator inserts. P/U and M/U dual side entry assembly. R/U cement hoses and chicksans and tested the lines to 7;000 psi. Pressure test BOPs F/ DCP Blue pod to 300/6;000 psi for 5/5/ min each w/ 13.8 ppg SBM - Annulars to 300/2800 for 5/5 min each-good tests and Function test. Layout double dutch. Function diverter and RIH t/ 27;640' filling the pipe. Take pump rates and drop ball to activate open jet tech. Performed 3 passes jetting the BOPs while pumping down boost line and lower kill line @ 17 bpm w/ 2;427 psi.

Sat 6.10 -Function BOP rams and annulars. Jet BOPs again while pumping down the boost line. Drop Jet tech ball and record pump rates to confirm closure. Run back in hole to 27;792' MD. Online cleaning. End of 7RRR Drilling. "},{"   ":276,"WELL_NAME":"SN207","API12":608124011700,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-06-11","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 6.11 - Continue to displace well to 14 ppg CaBr2 (14.01 DHE). R/U Franks equipment and Supreme handling tools. P/U and run ESTMZ open hole guide shoe latch assembly and washpipe.

Thurs 6.15 - Continue to RIH w/ HES lower completion assembly. P/U; M/U and RIH w/ ESTMZ zone # 4 assembly and tested it. Then zone #3; zone #2 and zone #1 assemblies. P/U and RIH with suspension latch (fishing string).

Fri 6.16 - Continue to RIH w/ suspension latch tool t/ 2;338' and latched into receptacle with 15k down. Observed weight increase of 22k indicating the ratch latch was engaged. POOH w/ suspension tool shearing pin w/ 5k overpull. Continue to POOH to surface. L/D retrieving tool; suspension tool; close shifter and marked washpipe. P/T the entire system to 250 psi/3 min. service tool to 250 psi/3 min. R/D the becket and bails and R/U TTM-585 elevators. P/U and RIH w/ VCH Frac Packer Assembly and continue to TIH w/ ESTMZ assembly. F/T BOPs.

Mon 6.19 - Set RTTS @10;620'; Perform Positive to 1;500 psi for 15 min/Perform negative test; pump 268 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil down drill pipe with cement unit to achieve 3;350 psi; close mvbr and sstv; apply 2;500 psi down kill line between rams with rig pumps; cementer bleed pressure down to 0 psi in 500 psi increments; HPHT decreased from 2;828 psi to -536 psi. Tue 6.20 - Wait on Weather

Wed 6.21 - Wait on weather; TIH and Test BOP's F/ TCP yellow pod to 300/8800 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 8.6 ppg

Thurs 6.22 - Continue testing BOP's - Annulars to 6;200 psi high for 5/5 minutes each. Sub Sea function test BOPs on 4 1/2" profile from DCP Blue. Performed full diverter function from TCP (All tests Good). Displace Riser from SW to CaBr2. POOH and L/D. PU RTTS RT and TIH

Fri 6.23 - POOH with Blackhawk storm packer. Perform casing pressure test with 14.0 ppg Brine T/6;000 psi high for 30 minutes. TIH with lower completion wash pipe at 1.5 min/stand  T/20;476'.

Sat 6.24 - TIH with inner string to lower completion. Pressure test closed system to 3;500 psi. Open MJPS and inject at 2;250 psi.

Thurs 6.29 - R/D Frac iron and POOH with service tool. Function test BOPs from DCP / Blue and Diverter F/DCP . Continue POOH. L/D BHA.

Mon 7.3 - POOH with Halliburton Service Tool. Shut down due to fire and gas system fault and troubleshoot same. Perform planned rig maintenance. Wait on and receive BSEE approval to resume operations after resolving fault issue. POOH with Halliburton Service tool.

Tue 7.4 - R/U handling equipment for ESTMZ production isolation BHA. Function UBSR and LBSR F/TCP blue and DCP yellow pod. P/U and RIH with Production Isolation string.

Wed 7.5 - Continue to RIH with Production Isolation String. Thurs 7.6- Released PO tool. Reverse Circulate. Sting out of HCH packer. P/U and pull wear bushing. P/U and jet BOPs. Boost riser. Pump spike fluid. Repair Top drive

We 05/04/16 - POOH/LD LDB RT/diverter sub. Pulled/LD diverter. Performed brake test/OK. Unlatched BOP's/cleaned WH. Installed trash cap on WH 10' AML. Moved rig to safe zone. Secured tensioner rig. Removed turn down sheaves/drape hoses/secured.

Th 05/05/16 - LD landing jt. Pulled/LD slip jt. Commence POOH w/riser/BOP's F/9521' to 4259'MD.

Fr 05/06/16 - Completed POOH/LD riser/BOP's/skidded to transport. RD riser handling equip. 

Sa 05/07/16 - Installed THS/tested gasket to 13400 psi/OK. Installed TA 15' AML. Performed general rig maintenance/housekeeping. WORK COMPLETED - WELL IS T/A - WAITING ON APD APPROVAL FOR STONES 011 ST 00 BP 00 TO MOVE RIG - FINAL REPORT.



"},{"   ":296,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-02-04","TEXT_REMARK":"Sat 2.4.2017 - Broke circulation down c/k lines after latch up and filled riser. Conducted LBSR and connector pressure tests 300/8;800 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 8.6 ppg sea water. Performed casing test to 8;800 psi for 30 minutes all test performed with 8.6 ppg sea water. Performed EDS fire test. Unlatched and cleaned and prepped stabs prior to changing out ring gasket."},{"   ":297,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-02-05","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 2.5 - Finish N/U BOP and change AX ring gasket. Complete autoshear test. Complete UBSR tests . Functioned casing shear rams and performed acoustic function testing of UBSR; CSR; LBSR. RIH with 8.5" Cleanout Assembly to BOP. Space out and test BOPs on 4.5" pipe to 300/ 8;800 psi for 5/5 minutes each. Test upper annular and associated valves 300/ 5;500 psi for 5/5 minutes each. All test performed using 8.6 ppg sea water.

Mon 2.6 -  Completed BOP pressure and function testing on 4 1/2" drill pipe F/ TCP yellow pod & F/ SCP blue pod and performed accumulator draw down test. TIH to tag surface cement plug at 10;836' MD/TVD. Drill Cement F/10;833' T/11;110'.

Tue 2.7 - RIH with 8.5" Cleanout Assembly and tag FasDrill. Circulate bottoms up. R/U and perform casing pressure test to 5;000 psi for 30 minutes using 13.2 ppg (13.42ppg DH) SOBM;. R/D testing equipment and begin RIH to tag FasDrill.

Wed 2.8 - Drill FasDrill plug and slack off to TOL at 22;511' MD. Circulate hole clean and POOH with 8.5" Cleanout Assembly. RIH with 6.5" Cleanout Assembly.

Thurs 2.9 - TIH with 6.5" Cleanout Assembly. Drill remainder of FasDrill to TOL and continue TIH. Tag EZSV at 25;612' and circulate bottoms up. R/U and conduct 10 1/8" x 10 3/4" and 7 5/8" Casing Pressure Test to 2;960 psi with 13.2 ppg (13.42ppg DH) sbm for 30 min. against cast iron bridge plug at 25'612' MD. Begin drilling EZSV.

Fri 2.10 - Drilled through EZSV and 10 ft of new formation T/25;819'. Circulate bottoms up. R/U to perform FIT. Pump up PWD readings and conduct FIT to 2;115 psi. Perform FIT at 7.625" shoe set at 25;809 ft MD / 25;393 ft TVD with 13.2 ppg surface MW SBM (13.42 ppg static down hole MW) using Schlumberger cement unit for pressure on chart. Data was received from PWD indicating 15.06 ppg. Flow checked the well prior to POOH T/ 12;621'.

Sat 2.11 - POOH with 6.5" Cleanout Assembly. Slip and cut drill line and maintenance and change out of encoder. P/U Champ Packer and RIH with same T/18;244'."},{"   ":298,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-02-12","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 2.12 - RIH with Champ Packer and attempt to set packer. Did not set. POOH with Champ Packer; clean magnets; and examine packer. Prepare drillstring by P/U magnets and 5-7/8" DP. Wait on BlackHawk Packer.

Mon 2.13 - RIH with Blackhawk HD packer and set at 22;494'. Pressure tested 10-3/4" x 10-1/8" Casing to 6;500 psi for 30 minutes w/13.2 SMW (13.4 DHE). Good Test. Retrieved packer and POOH T/2;770'. Function BOPs and diverter.

Tue 2.14 - POOH w/ Blackhawk packer. P/U and RIH w/ 6.5" Drilling BHA. Shallow test. RIH to BOPs. Function BSRs. Begin slip and cut drill line and repair top drive leak.

Wed 2.15 - Finished repairing top drive o-ring leak. Calibrate block and brake test. RIH w/ BHA to current hole depth (logged pip tags). Gathered SCR parameters and drill F/ 25;819' T/ 26;040' MD.

Thurs 2.16 - Drill F/ 26;040' MD T/ 26;804' MD. Decide to POOH to swap 6.5" BHA components due to directional issues. Begin circulating 13.6 ppg (13.8 DHE) around.

Fri 2.17 - Finish displacement to 13.6 ppg. Pump out of hole to shoe. Pull wet to liner top. Pump slug and POOH dry to surface.

Sat 2.18 - POOH to surface w/ 6.5" BHA. Plug into MWD/DD tools. Swap out Powerdrive and Impulse. RIH w/ new 6.5" BHA. Spaceout and begin BOP testing on 4.5". (Annulars and Rams not yet tested)"},{"   ":299,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-02-19","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 2.19 - Test BOPs on 4.5" DP. (Test MVBR; LVBR and all associated choke manifold
valves and fails safes to 300/ 6;500 psi for 5/5 minutes each. Test upper annular; lower annular and associated valves 300/ 3;200 psi for 5/5 minutes each. All test performed using 13.6 ppg SBM (13.8 DHE). Subsea function test BOP F/ DCP blue pod. Subsea function test Diverter F/ DCP. RIH T/ 26;804'. Drill ahead w/ 6.5" BHA T/27;324' MD (26;835' TVD).

Mon 2.20 - Drill ahead with 6.5" BHA to 27;840 MD (27;326 TVD). Confirmed this as TD. Begin circulating hole clean. (weight up from 13.6 ppg to 13.8 ppg (14.0 DHE). 

Tue 2.21 - Make Check trip to bottom; Circulate and condition hole; Pump out the othe hole to 7 5/8" TOL. Circulate Bottom up

Wed 2.22 - Continue circulating BU at 7 5/8" TOL; Pull 10 stands wet; Pump slug and POOH; L/D 6.5" BHA; Slip and cut drill line and service rig

Thurs 2.23 - Continue C/O Saver sub; Rig up to run lower Completion; Run lower completion

Fri 2.24 - Continue running Lower Completion; Run Lower completion on Landing string

Sat 2.25 - RIH with Lower Completion; Set SB3 Packer @22;460' MD and test backside to 2;500 psi for 15 min.; Set down 80K and apply 3;800 psi down string with cement unit and hold for 15 min. Release from packer; Circulate BU 13.8 SBM; Clean mud pumps and suface lines. Function diverter from TCP."},{"   ":300,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-02-26","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 2.26 - Displace to 14 ppg CaBr2 Brine; Clean surface equipment - **Note - Brine is the same weight surf/downhole**

Mon 2.27 - Filter Brine; RU Frac head

Tue 2.28 - R/U Coflex hoses and control lines to frac head. Space out per Baker. Begin pressure testing lines. Shift P-sleeve and perform injection rates. Transferred 14.0 ppg brine to Stim Star IV. Observed leak on Coflex hose from rig floor to main deck. Wait on Concentric Coflex hose and monitor well.


Wed 3.1 - Wait on Concentric Coflex Hose. Offload Hose; R/U same. Flush line with 82 bbls of seawater and pressure test lines from frac boat to frac head. Decision made to wait on weather prior to beginning frac job.

Thurs 3.2 - Wait on Weather. R/D ball launcher. M/U TIWs and IBOPs to pressure test.

Fri 3.3 - Wait on weather. Monitor workstring and casing pressure. Bled tubing pressure from 1;580 psi to 1;000 psi and stripped up 7 feet through annular. Bled backside pressure from 500 psi to 0 psi. Test BOP on 6-5/8" DP w/ 14.0 Brine fluid F/ DCP blue pod- Pipe rams & associated failsafe 300/6;000 psi 5/5 mins. Good Test.

Sat 3.4 -  Wait on weather. Perform BOP test on 6-5/8" DP to 300/6;000 psi and 300/2;800 psi for annulars and associated failsafe w/ 14.0 Brine fluid F/ DCP
blue pod. Perform BOP function test from TCP/yellow. Subsea function test diverter from DCP.

"},{"   ":301,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-03-05","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 3.5 - Wait on Weather. Monitor well. Attempt to bring Stim Star in but weather conditions still causing Stim Star to go into yellow.

Mon 3.6 - Wait on Weather. Stim Star IV and Centerline moved into position and connected hoses. Installed Oil States 3-Way Spool and flush lines to ball launcher with 8.3 ppg drill water. Pressure test ball launcher upper and lower valves T/ 300/14;300psi 5/5 mins. with 8.3 ppg drill water from cement unit.

Tue 3.7 - Pressure test and flush lines to 300/14;700 psi 5/5 mins. Re-perform injection test. Perform mini frac and frac analysis. Perform treatment 1-7.

Wed 3.8 - Complete Treatment 6-9. Swap hoses from HOS Centerline to Agnes Candies. Stim Star 4 performed pump maintenance. Continue with Treatment 10 and continue through Treatment 12.

Thurs 3.9 - Completed Frac Stages. Closed IB4 and reverse circulated with 14.0 ppg Brine. Pressure tested IB4 with 14ppg CaBr T/ 3;800psi; (1;500psi over ISIP-2;300 psi);. Flow checked well. Pumped 59 bbls 14.4 ppg Brine slug while R/D surface equipment. Began L/D Frac head and Coflex Hose.

Fri 3.10 - Pumped 14.4 ppg slug/ R/D Frac Head and Coflex Hose. POOH to test Kelly Hose and IBOPS. Replace leaky swivel packing. POOH with completion service tool and washpipe; stopping to function test BOP's and diverter on 5-7/8" DP. POOH above BOPs to function LBSR & UBSR. Continue POOH.

Sat 3.11 - Finishes slip/cut and servicing rig. M/U BSRTT and RIH with same. Engage seal; disengage and perform UBSR and LBSR pressure test F/ TCP yellow B; all test performed to 300/6;000 psi for 5/5 minutes each using 14.0 ppg CaBr2 (Brine same DHE). Engage BSRTT and POOH."},{"   ":302,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-03-12","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 3.12 - POOH with BSRTT. Instal 15' pup on Spanner joint and L/D same on riser deck. P/U intermediate completion assemblies and RIH with same. R/D Frank's equipment and run assemblies on 4-1/2" and 5-7/8" DP. Subsea function tested UBSR and LBSR. Began spacing out for BOP testing.

Mon 3.13 - Finished testing BOPs. All test performed with 14.0 ppg CaBr2. Test UVBR; MVBR; LVBR; Kelly Hose; Top drive upper IBOP; Top Drive Lower IBOP; 2 6 5/8" GTM 69 TIW; 5 7/8" TTM 585 TIW; 5 7/8" TTM585 IBOP; 6 5/8" GTM 69 IBOP and all associated fail safes and choke manifold valves 300/6000 psi for 5/5 minutes each.  Test upper annular and all associated valves 300/2800 psi 5/5 minutes each. RIH with intermediate assemblies on 5-7/8" DP. Ran 1 WorkTech stand and finished RIH on 6-5/8" DP. Attempt to circulate through chicksan and side entry sub. B/O stand and circulate through top drive with success. S/O to attempt to shift IB4.

Tue 3.14 - Drop ball to release PO running tool. Pressure up and release PO tool. P/U and close FS-2. Blow ball seat. Pressure tested E-22 locator seal assembly; SB-3 and FS2 valve to 2;500 psi using 14.0 ppg CaBr2 and charted for 15 minutes. Circulate surface to surface. Flush stack. Pull WB and flush profile. Continue circulate riser volume. POOH T/ 16;066' MD.

Wed 3.15 - POOH w/ intermediate running tools and L/D same. R/U Frank's tongs for upper completion. RIH w/ Ratch-Latch; LSOTJ; Wireline Guide; and HHS Packer assemblies.

Thurs 3.16 - P/U and RIH w/ CID and PDHPG. Continued RIH w/ 18.9# 4.5" tubing to BOP stack. Functioned UBSR and LBSRs. Continued RIH w/ tubing. P/U and RIH w/ SLB safety valve. Continue RIH T/ 9;669' MD.

Fri 3.17 - RIH w/ 18.9# 4.5" tubing. M/U and terminate control lines in tubing hanger. Installed Frank's cobra arm and slips. Begin RIH on 6-5/8" GTM-69.

Sat 3.18 - RIH w/ upper completion F/ 12;685' T/ 22;269' MD. Landed out upper completion. Locked in tubing hanger as per FMC. Rigged up to test SCSSSV."},{"   ":303,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-03-19","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 3.19 - Reverse in 12.0 ppg packer fluid. Set production packer- Packer depth 21;901' MD; 21;645' TVD. Negative test production packer- SLB bled dp F/4;400 psi T/ 3;800 psi & perform 5;000 psi negative test on the production packer @ 21;901 MD (21;645 TVD) hold F/ 15 min on chart (see SLB chart)-(12.0 ppg packer fluid) Good Test Attempt SCSSSV negative test; no success closing valve fully. Troubleshoot SCSSSV.

Mon 3.20 - Cycle SCSSSV. Vent control lines for 4 hours. Pressure up landing string to 5;000 psi and bleed down to attempt closure of SCSSSV. No success. Wait on e-line / slickline. Continue to cycle SV1 / SV2 on SCSSSV.

Tue 3.21 - Continue cycling SV1 / SV2 while waiting on slickline / E-line. Perform casing / packer test to 7;100 psi with slb with 12.0 ppg CaBr f/ 30 mins. Tested AAV T/ 2;000 psi for 15 min using 12.0 ppg CaBr w/ ROV support. Displace riser to seawater.

Wed 3.22 - Displace riser to seawater. Successfully close SCSSSV. Negative test of 1;200 psi - successful. (SLB pressure up 1;200 psi down drill pipe with 14 ppg CaBr. SLB cement unit bump pressure on drill pipe up to 1;228 psi with 14.0 ppg CaBr. DPG-16;842 psi. IWOCS verified SV 1& 2 vented. SLB bled pressure F/1;228 T/ 973 psi on drill pipe; observed pressure below SCSSSV remain static @ 16;838 psi. (1;228 trapped below SCSSSV). SLB bled remaining pressure to 0 & performed 15 min no flow @ unit
(good no flow - charted negative test and WD graphs) Displace back to 14.0 ppg brine. Unlatch THRT. Displace back to seawater. POOH w/ THRT. 

Thurs 3.23 - Finish POOH w/ THRT. R/D THRT and upper completion surface equipment. R/U for riser pulling. Unlatch BOPs and pull clear of wellhead.

Fri 3.24 - Move rig to safe zone. Pull riser to 9;000' while ROV and tree are lowered to 8;950'. Move rig back to well center. Lower tree onto wellhead. Land; lock; and test tree to 13;500psi. Move rig back to safe zone. Continue pulling riser.**JOB COMPLETE**"},{"   ":304,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-10-26","TEXT_REMARK":"Thur 10.26 - Performed field arrival procedures. ROV set beacons.Test fit Logan's track dolly on the AUX side. TOI completed DP trials. ROV performed bottom survey. Offloaded project equipment from OSV.

Fri 10.27 - M/U tapered stress joint and dress with XTM-57 and annulus pipe joints. Terminate riser angle inclinometer to EDP and TSJ. Lower TSJ and annulus pipe through the rotary.Skid OWIRS stack to well center. Make up speedloc to EDP. Unlock LRP from test stump and replace with inspection cart. Drift production bore; TSJ to LRP w/ 4" drift. Splash OWIRS. P/T TSJ connection. Run OWIRS on XTM-57 DP and 2 3/8" annulus tubing to 2;032'.

Sat 10.28 - Troubleshoot FMC's RCS unit. Continue to TIH with OWIRS on 5 7/8" DP and 2 3/8" annulus tubing from 2;032' to 5;023'. R/U test assembly and performed wet integrity test on 5 7/8" DP and 2 3/8" annulus tubing to 300 psi low and 8;400 psi high. R/D test iron and continue to TIH with OWIRS package from 5;023' to 8;251'."},{"   ":305,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-10-29","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 10.29 - Continue to TIH with OWIRS from 8;251' to 9;600'. Move rig from safe zone to 50' from well center and perform dummy spaceout. Move to safe zone and install necessary DP and annulus pipe per spaceout. P/T DP riser and annulus tbg to 300 psi and 8;400psi for 5 min each. Removed kelly hose and side drape bumper guards. P/U and R/U upper CCTLF. P/U and RU lower CCTLF. R/U hoses and umbilicals for CCTLF.

Mon 10.30 - Continue to R/U CCTLF air hoses. Installed 750 bails. P/U CCTLF to engage track dolly. Connected hydraulic control lines to Logan's panel. Functioned test Logan CCTLF. P/U and M/U upper riser crossover. Connected Frank's elevators to 750 ton bails. P/U and M/U surface tree; swivel and transition joint assembly speedloc to riser crossover. Connected control lines and F/T SFT. Performed integrity
test on SFT; 5 7/8" DP and 2 3/8" tubing. P/U and stab H.E.S CT BOPs on SFT and nipple up same. R/U temporary iron on CT BOP to Expro choke manifold. R/U CT BOP control lines.

Tue 10.31- While waiting on boat to arrive; continue to R/U CT BOP control lines and R/U temporaty iron on rig floor. P/U and M/U riser spools and hydra-conn. Stab CT into injector head. M/U DSA CT connector and performed pull test DSA CT connector. Continue to R/U temporary iron on CT unit. Attempted to P/U injector head and install onto CCTLF porch - not enough clearance. Logan lowered CCTLF porch to allow clearance.

Wed 11.1 - Continue to adjust Logan CCTLF porch. P/U injector head onto CCTLF porch. Fill CT with SW. Performed CT test #1 to to 300/11;500 psi. Performed CT BOP; choke manifold and other surface equipment test #2 to 300/8;400 psi.

Thurs 11.2 - Continue testing CT BOP; Choke manifold and other surface equipment to 300 psi/8;400 psi. Unlock Hydra-conn and skid injector head back from well center. P/U wireline valves; stab into hydra-conn and lock same. Function test wireline valves. M/U wireline pressure test BHA. R/U wireline sheaves; lubricator.

Fri 11.3 - Pressure test wireline lubricator to 300 psi/8;400 psi for 5 min each. Disconnect QTS and L/D lubricator and toolstring. Installed night cap. Lined up rig pumps on5 7/8" DP riser and 2 3/8" annulus and flushed each string. Rig moved to WC. Landed OWIRS on XT and performed intial latch up procedure. Transferred weight to Logan CCTLF. ROV installed HFL and established communication with XT. Started on bottom OWIRS pressure test to 300 psi and 8;400 psi for 5 min each. Repaired a leak on rig's choke manifold.

Sat 11.4 - Continue to perform on bottom OWIRS pressure test to 300 psi and 8;400 psi for 5 min each. Performed accumulator drawdown test on OWIRS package. Displaced dual string riser to 12 ppg brine. ROV opened ASV. FMC opened AMV. Applied 1000 psi down the annulus and blocked iin ROV opened PSV. Equalizd across PMV and FMC commanded open PMV and SCSSV. Bullhead well with 12 ppg workover brine. R/U wireline PCE."},{"   ":306,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-11-05","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 11.5 - Pressure tested wireline PCE to 300 psi/ 8400 psi for 5 min each. M/U BHA and RIH to 26;921'. Tagged @ depth a few times but unable to pass through. POOH with wireline BHA. L/D lubritcator and BHA. M/U 2.70" motor/mill CT BHA. Pressure test CT PCE.

Mon 11.6 - Establish circulation rates. RIH with CT at ~ 50 fpm breaking circulation evey 1;000 ft. FMC opened PRV; Expro closed choke. FMC open RPIV. Continue to RIH with CT @ 50 fpm maintaining constant BHP. At 21;721 ft. HES CT obtained circulating rates. Started to wash down to 26;942 ft. maintaining constant BHP. RIH w/ 2.70'' Mill Assy @ 20ft/min F/ 26;942ft. T/ 26;947ft. Mill obstruction in well F/
26;947 ft. T/ 26;948 ft and worked string while pumping sweep. Noticed 26Bbl gain in volume. Bullhead 40 bbls of 12 ppg brine. Shut down and check presures. Bullhead 30 bbs of 12 ppg brine. Shut down and checked final pressures. Circulate BU.

Tue 11.7 - Circulate 12.0 ppg Brine while building gelled brine. RIH F/26;424' T/ 26;680' while pumping 12.0 ppg gelled brine. Continue RIH and mill obstruction F/ 27;105' T/27;106'. Observe oil saturation in brine returns. Continue pumping 12.0 ppg gelled fluid. Build clean 12.0 ppg Brine and transfer to active tank.

Wed 11.8 - Perform pit management. Pump slick 12.0 ppg brine. Wash down T/27;142'. POOH while pumping slick brine. Run back in hole to continue milling at obstruction. POOH to 26;737' and shut down pump and close choke. Pump out MPT tanks; offload MPT tanks; filter brine as necessary; drain MI Swaco tanks. RIH and mill F/27;187' T/27;27;187.6'. POOH with CT.

Thurs 11.9 - POOH with CT. Close and trap pressure between RPIV and PRV with CT above OWIRS. Bleed pressure and continue POOH. B/O Hydra-conn and B/O BHA. Replace motor and mill while cutting CT. Perform CT BOP function test. Pull test connector. Pressure test connector to 300 psi low for 5 min and 11;500 psi for 10 min (good
test) with 12.0ppg Brine ; DFCV; and Hydra-conn. Hold well control drill. M/U and RIH with BHA.

Fri 11.10 - RIH with CT and milled obstruction F/ 27;115' T/27;118' (Lower sleeve in stage 11). RIH and attempted to mill obstruction at 27;148'. POOH above lower completion to repair CT pump and replace primary stripper. RIH and attempt to mill at same obstruction (top sleeve of stage 10). POOH with CT.

Sat 11.11 - POOH with CT and replace BHA. Stab BHA into Hydra-Conn; Perform pressure test on Hydra-Conn; Stripper; and DFCV on H.E.S CT with SLB cement unit while H.E.S. CT unit held 3;500 psi internal pressure during high test; 300 psi low for 5min and held high test to 8;400 psi for 5min. Good Test. ; Conduct pressure test on CT; CT. connector to 300 psi low for 5 min and 11;500 psi for 10 min with 12.0 ppg Brine; Good Test. RIH with CT."},{"   ":307,"WELL_NAME":"SN208","API12":608124010400,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-11-12","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 11.12 - RIH with CT T/ 27;143' CTM. Milled through top of stage 10 F/ 27;143' CTM T/ 27;146' CTM and slacked off and attempted to mill at bottom seat of stage 10. P/U and run back in and tag a 27;146'. Pump gel sweep and POOH with CT while pumping.

Mon 11.13 - POOH with CT to surface. L/D BHA and cut 200' of coil. Install CT connector and pull test same. Pressure test CT and CT connector to 300 psi low for 5min and 11;500 psi for 10 min with 12.0 ppg Brine. Wait on additional BHA equipment (oscillator). Stage oscillator and wait on weather to perform man riding operations to M/U and stab in BHA.

Tue 11.14 - Wait on weather. M/U BHA and stab into Hydraconn and pressure test same 300psi low 5min; T/ 8;400psi 5min. (Good Test).. RIH with CT and tag bottom of stage 10 at 27;141'. Mill through 6 seats (bottom 10 through top of 7).

Wed 11.15 - Milled through top of stage 7 through bottom of stage 4 (8 seats). Wash down and tag top of stage 3 at 27;550'. Pump 3 bbl 12.0 ppg gel sweep and displace with brine. Perform drift run F/ 27;550 T/ 26;795'. Pump 30 bbl pill and displace with 12.0 ppg brine while working pipe F/ 27;550' T/ 26;220' and downT/26;400'.

Thurs 11.16 - Circulate 30 bbl gel sweep out of well and notice fine solids in the returns. Pump additional 40 bbl gel pill and circulate out of hole while POOH to ~26;500' monitoring returns. Pump 140 bbl formic acid. Bullhead with 9.45 ppg formic acid followed by 12.0 ppg brine. POOH to 26;000' and shut in well and monitor pressure while waiting on acid.

Fri 11.17 - Complete bullheading of formic acid. POOH with CT and secure well. L/D CT BHA. R/D injector head. Flush lines and begin riser displacement to seawater.

Sat 11.18 - Displaced riser from 12 ppg to brine to 8.6 ppg seawater. Bled off pressure on Expro choke and perform a good no flow test. FMC removed EFLs; HFLs; and aligned valves for disconnect. Unlatch OWIRs. R/D surface equipment while ROV installed HFLs; tree cap and tested same. Installed SFL to SST; turned over tree to host; and recovered beacons. Moved to Stones SN110 **JOB COMPLETE**"},{"   ":308,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-05","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 04/01:  Transit to WR 508 No 14. ETA 04/02/2018 at 15:00 hrs.

Mon 04/02: Transit to Stones WR 508 No 14. Arrive on location at 18:24 hrs.

Tues 04/03: ROV perform clear bottom survey and deploy beacons.

** Verbal Approval for Jetting Operations by Mr. Bobby Nelson

Wed 04/04: Continue DP trials & tuning.

Thurs 04/05: P/U 36" LPWHH jt & M/U.  RIH w/ jetting BHA (11" stick out). RIH w/ jetting assy T/ 500' above ML. Verify bullseye & position rig. Tag seabed at 9;685' RKB at 15:30 hrs. Jet 36" conductor T/ 9;881' (14' stick up). Let 36" soak.

**  Verbal Approval to start 28" operations by Mr. Bobby Nelson

Fri 04/06: Soak 36". Release FMC DAT & drill 29.8" x 32.5" T/ 11;120'. At TD; pumped sweeps & pumped OOH. Washed WH w/ PBL. Stab 28" csg in WH & RIH. R/U lines & land out 28" (10995' MD/TVD). 

Sat 04/07: Perform 28" casing cement job. 13.0 ppg Class A 2;549 cuft; Dye first 20 bbls of lead slurry. observed green dye at WH at 140 bbls of tail slurry pumped. measured 12.9 ppg w/ pH meter. 28" casing shoe 10;995' MD/TVD. POOH w/ 29.8" x 32.5" BHA & reconfigure for 26" BHA. RIH w/ 26" BHA. RIH & wash to bottom. Tag cement at 10;909'. Drill out cement & rathole T/ 11;120'. Circ B/U; pump OOH; POOH"},{"   ":309,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-08","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 04/08:  Stab BHA in WH. Wash down to bottom & drill ahead w/ 26" BHA T/ 13;206' w/ 8.6 ppg SW.

Mon 04/09: Drill 26" to TD at 14;540' switching to 11.0 ppg WBM at 14;000'. At TD pump sweeps & circulate B/U w/ 13.0 ppg WBM. Back ream out of hole w/ 13.0 ppg WBM & wash WH w/ PBL. POOH above WH.

Tues 04/10: RIH w/ 22" casing on landing string and land out in WH w/ 50k down @ 06:30hrs. Shoe depth 14;489' MD/TVD. Pump cement job as per Halliburton (13.3 ppg Class A cement; 6;805 cu. ft. cement total; displace w/ 320 bbls seawater). Cement in Place @ 13:17 hrs. Set FMC seal assembly and test to 1;000 psi for 2 minutes. POOH w/ inner string.

Wed 04/11: splash BOP at 08:15hrs. RIH w/ BOP on riser T/ 360' before testing choke/kill lines to 250-350psi low and 11;000psi high. Test boost and rigid conduit lines to 250-350psi low and 5;000psi high (good tests). Continue to run BOP on riser.

Thurs 04/12: Continue to run BOP on riser T/ 9;509'.

Fri 04/13: latch into tensioner ring and transfer all weight to tensioners. Install diverter and rig down riser running equipment. P/U BLAT tool and land BOP at 22:00 hrs.

Sat 04/14: Pressure test 22" casing with 8.6 ppg. seawater to 4;500psi. P/U tailpipe and FMC SLT/BSRTT and RIH w/ same to test BOPs. Land out test tool and pressure test BOPs from DCP on Blue POD. Annulars tested to 7;000 psi; rams tested to 9;100 psi; and wellhead connector tested to 11;600 psi. Perform deadman auto shear function; diverter flow through test; and accumulator drawdown. Function test BOPs on 6-5/8" drillpipe from TCP on Yellow POD and diverter from DCP (41 sec). Unseat test plug and POOH.  (good tests)

"},{"   ":310,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-15","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 04/15:  Finish POOH. Wait on weather. Seas 9-12' and winds 30-40 knots throughout day.

Mon 04/16: RIH w/ 18-1/8" x 21" BHA. Continue to RIH and tag TOC @ 14;347'. Begin to displace choke; kill; and boost lines to 9.8ppg surface MW.

Tues 04/17: Displace C/K/B to 9.8 ppg surface wt SBM. Displace drillstring and wellbore to 9.8 ppg surface wt SBM while drilling cement shoetrack. Perform choke drill prior to drilling 10' new formation to 14;550' and conducting FIT. FIT performed at 22" casing shoe (14;489' TVD) with 10.19 ppg static DHMW. Pump at 1/4 bbl per minute to 762psi surface pressure. Calculated 11.2 ppg EMW. MWD pumped up max 11.11 ppg EMW. 6 bbls pumped; 6 bbls bled back. Drill ahead with 18.125" x 21" BHA T/ 15;451' MD.

Wed 04/18: Drill ahead T/ 18;494'

Thurs 04/19: Drill ahead T/ 20;990'. weight up active mud system from 9.8ppg to 10.0ppg surface weight. (10.4 DHEMW)

Fri 04/20: Drill ahead  T/ 23;375'

Sat 04/21: Drill ahead T/ 23;600' MD; 22;796' TVD (section TD). Pump 200 bbl Hi-Vis sweep and follow with 10.3 ppg surface wt. mud to circulate well clean. Weight up to 10.4 ppg surface (10.6 ppg DHEMW) and displace well. Begin to pump out of hole. Function test BOPs from TCP on Blue POD and Diverter from TCP
"},{"   ":311,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-22","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 04/22:  Pump out of hole T/ 18;800' before pulling wet T/ 14;557' (just below 22" shoe).

Mon 04/23: P/U casing doubles from deck and start to run liner T/ 18;400'.

Tues 04/24: RIH w/ 16" casing T/ 22;872' MD / 22;149' TVD. 16" Liner top 13;295'MD/TVD. Perform 16" cement job w/ 3873 cuft (class A 13.3 ppg) Rig pumps displace w/ 2255 bbls SBM. No indication of top plug landing. Cement in place at 21:50 hrs.  Losses observed.

A. Explanation of lost returns (full loss; partial loss; etc) - partial losses (1.93% of total job)
B. Were there any operational issues -  No
C. How was loss of returns indicated - 60 bbl difference from displacement pit to the returns pit
D. How much cement was pumped versus approved in APD - 3;873 cuft pumped / 3;673 cuft in APD
E. What was lift pressure - 1;493 psi
F. What is TOC and how has this been calculated - TOC is estimated at 16;031 ft MD from lift pressure and Halliburton pressure match models in line with an under gauge hole 

Wed 04/25: Continue WOC. POOH T/ surface. R/U 3.5" handling equipment. P/U 3.5" stinger doubles and RIH.

Thurs 04/26:  RIH w/ 3.5" stinger on 6-5/8" DP to above TOL. Take friction & injection rates w/ cement unit. Pump 60 bbls base oil down kill line for 500 psi differential. Perform 200 bbl liner top squeeze per Haillburton procedure (15.6 ppg Class A; 1123 cubic feet of cement) placing 85 bbls base oil in DP. WOC

Fri 04/27: Continue WOC.  Perform 1000 psi pressure test at liner top (good test). Wash down to 13;356' & circulate string volume. POOH wet T/ surface and L/D 3-1/2" stinger. Function test UBSR & LBSR and perform casing test to 4000 psi for 30 min with 10.7 ppg downhole MW for 30 minutes (good test).while completing planned maintenance on rig floor. Slip & cut drill line and pressure test LBSR's from Toolpusher (Secondary) panel; Yellow Pod to 250 psi low; 4000 psi high with Halliburton cement unit with 10.7 ppg downhole MW.

Sat 04/28: Pressure test UBSR's from Toolpusher (Secondary) panel Yellow Pod to 250 psi low; 4000 psi high with Halliburton cement unit; 10.4 ppg SBM. Function test UBSR & LBSR from Drillers (Primary) panel yellow Pod. TIH w/ 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" BHA & set FMC wear bushing in wellhead. Continue TIH & pressure test BOP's and annular on 5-7/8" DP with 250/350 psi low; 6400 psi high with 10.4 ppg surface MW. Good Test . Function test BOP's & Diverter. Continue TIH w/ 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" BHA F/ 11;611' T/ 20;450' washing down through 16" liner top."},{"   ":312,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-29","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 04/29:  TIH w/ 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" BHA. Tagged firm cement at 22;732'. Drill out cement; rathole; & 10' new formation T/ 23;610'. Back ream to shoe and circulate. Performed LOT with 10.82 ppg ESD (Surface MW of 10.5 ppg) to 3555 psi for EMW = 13.9 ppg @ 22;149' shoe TVD. TIH back to bottom and drill ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" T/ 23;813'.

Mon 04/30: Drill ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" hole T/ 24;233'. P/U & close reamer; drill 10'. P/U & open reamer. Continue drilling ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" hole T/ 24;430'.

Tues 05/01: Drill ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" hole T/ 24;998' following weight up schedule. Weighting up from 10.6 to 11.8 DHEMW.

Wed 05/02: Drill ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" hole T/ 25;516' following weight up schedule. Weight up mud system as per drilling program to 12.0 ppg SBM (12.4 DHEMW).

Thurs 05/03: Drill ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" hole T/ 26;057' following weight up schedule. Weight up mud system as per drilling program to 13.0 ppg SBM (13.3 DHEMW)

Fri 05/04: Drill ahead 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" hole T/ 26;595' and call section TD (26595' MD / 25355' TVD) Circulate hole clean.

Sat 05/05: Circulate hole clean w/ 13.05 ppg surface MW. Record ESD of 13.28 ppg. Pump out of hole to 13;218' (above 16" liner). Function test BOP's & diverter.

***On 05/05/18 at 18:03 hrs Rachael Sanford (Shell Engineer) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (Houma BSEE) to set and cement 14" casing higher than APD (26;480 ft MD/25;261 ft TVD).

"},{"   ":313,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-05-06","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 05/06: POOH w/ 14-1/2" x 17-1/2" BHA. 

Mon 05/07: POOH T/ surface w/ BHA. R/U Franks for 14" casing run. RIH w/ 14" casing T/ 6;189'.

Tues 05/08: P/U 14" casing doubles from riser deck and run T/ 6;898'. Continue running 14" casing stands out of derrick T/ 16;796'. P/U and M/U 14" hanger and rig down casing running equipment and rig up drill pipe handling equipment. Continue running 14" casing on 6-5/8" landing string  T/ 18;615'.

Wed 05/09: Continue running in hole with 14" casing to 26;480' MD / 25;261' TVD and land out hanger as per FMC procedure (1;520K casing wt and 20K down). Mix and pump cement as per Halliburton. 898cuft of cement at 15.6 ppg. Class A

A. Explanation of lost returns (full loss; partial loss; etc) - full loses
B. Were there any operational issues -  No
C. How was loss of returns indicated - no returns
D. How much cement was pumped versus approved in APD - 898 cuft pumped / 824 cuft in APD
E. What was lift pressure - 260 psi (only a few psi off from pre job model prediction)
F. What is TOC and how has this been calculated - TOC is estimated at 25;232 ft MD from lift pressure and Halliburton pressure match models 

Thurs 05/10: Displace cement with mud pumps at 8 bpm until cement in place at 02:40 hrs. Set seal assembly as per FMC and pressure test to 9;000 psi with cement unit. L/D cement head and OES tool to pump foam ball and 50 bbls nut plug. Pump 16ppg slug and POOH. M/U 12.25" BHA and RIH with same to 2 stands above BOP.  The nut plug was not pumped into open hole or during the cement job; it was pumped after releasing the running to for the sole purpose of aiding cleaning of the landing string

Fri 05/11: Test 14" casing and BSR's to 250psi low / 5;300psi high. Continue RIH w/ 12 1/4" BHA and set wear bushing as per FMC. RIH and log tracer material in cement behind pipe F/ 25;036' - T/ 25;778' (TOC logged at 25;500' MD / 24;452' TVD). POOH and space out 5-7/8" DP across stack and begin testing BOP from driller's panel on Blue POD.

Sat 05/12: Complete testing of BOP from DCP on Blue POD; 250psi low / 6;900psi high. Test annulars to 250psi low / 4;500psi high with 13.05ppg SBM.  Good Tests. Function test BOP from TCP on Yellow POD. Function test diverter in full auto sequence from DCP. Wash down and tag float collar at 26;392'. Drill out float collar; shoetrack; and 10' new formation while weighting up mud system. Pump out of hole into shoe and MWD pump up ESD of 13.66 (2x). Conduct FIT to 1;760psi surface pressure for 15ppg calculated EMW. 15.25bbls pumped/15.25bbls bled back. MWD pump up 14.89ppg ESD max. Drill ahead T/ 26;618' MD / 25;379' TVD while weighting up to 13.9ppg ESD.

"},{"   ":314,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-05-13","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 05/13: Drill 12-1/4" hole section T/ 27;900'. Weight up from 13.7ppg DHEMW to 13.9ppg DHEMW at 27;150' MD.

Mon 05/14: Drill 12.25" hole T/ 30;011'. At 30;011'; pump 100 bbl Hi-Vis sweep and circulate.

Tues 05/15: Drill ahead T/ 30;131' MD / 28;272' TVD(Well TD). Pump out of hole and begin taking formation pressures as per program with Baker TesTrak.

Wed 05/16: Pump out of hole; collecting formation pressure samples as per program with Baker TesTrak. Max PP observed was 13.9ppg @ sensor depth of 28;290' MD / 26;753' TVD. Continue to pump out of hole 

Thurs 05/17: Function tested BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from TCP on Blue POD. Continue pumping out of hole and close BSRs. Function Test Diverter on 5-7/8" DP from TCP 

Fri 05/18: With BSRs closed; POOH T/ Surface. RIH with 10-1/8" casing stands out of derrick T/ 9;122'.

Sat 05/19: Monitor well below closed UBSR. Begin RIH with 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing T/ 20;314'. R/D casing handling equipment and R/U DP handling equipment and OES flowback tool. P/U and M/U 10-3/4" casing hanger and seal assembly as per FMC.

***REGULATORY: On 5/19/18 there was a minor leak observed coming from a vent line on blue pod following an ROV inspection. Mrs. Rachael Sandford with Shell Engineering received approval @ 20:21 hrs. from Mr. Bobby Nelson of BSEE Houma District to continue operations of running casing and performing the primary cement job as planned.
"},{"   ":315,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-05-20","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 05/20: Continue rigging up DP handling equipment and begin running in hole with 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing on 6-5/8" 60# LS. RIH T/ 29;836'; and tagged up with 90K weight down. R/B stand; pick up string to 29;721'; and continue to work pipe while circulating bottoms up.

Mon 05/21: Flow check (well static). Wash down 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing string on 60# landing string T/ 30;008' MD / 28;171' TVD. 

Tues 05/22: Perform cement job per Halliburton procedure with 16.2 ppg Class H; 926 cubic feet of cement. Set seal assembly & test to 7000 psi per FMC procedure (good test). Circulate riser. POOH w/ landing string 

A. Explanation of lost returns (full loss; partial loss; etc) - partial; 1270 bbl lost during the cement job (1921 bbl pumped)
B. Were there any operational issues - losses
C. How was loss of returns indicated - returns in the pits
D. How much cement was pumped versus approved in APD - 926 cu ft pumped; 769 cu ft in APD
E. What was lift pressure - 100 psi
F. What is TOC and how has this been calculated - 28;550 MD/ 26;986 ft TVD by logging with SBT on wire


Wed 05/23:  P/U FMC LIT & 6-5/8" tail pipe and RIH on 5-7/8" DP. Function test BOP's on 6-5/8" tail pipe. L/O LIT and take impression per FMC. POOH T/ surface w/ FMC LIT & tail pipe; function diverter on way out.

Thurs 05/24: R/U wireline; P/U sonic tool string; & RIH T/ 29;770'. Perform sonic log. POOH w/ wireline T/ surface & L/D toolstring. Pressure test casing to 3000 psi (good test). P/U CIBP assy & RIH on 5-7/8" DP w/ FMC wear bushing. RIH

Fri 05/25:  Finish RIH w/ CIBP and set at 28;660' MD/ 27059 TVD. Tag w/ 15k down to verify. POOH 

*** Verbal Approval by Mr. Bobby Nelson regarding changes in CFlex Procedure

Sat 05/26: P/U C-flex cementing tool & RIH T/ 27;318'. Pressure test cups (good test). Latch into C-flex at 27;403' MD/ 26;022' TVD bit depth. Attempt to open C-flex; no indication. Attempt to inject and gain in trip tank.
"},{"   ":316,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-05-27","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 05/27: Open C-flex and attempt to inject at 0.5 bpm (2940 psi max pressure). Shear solid seat in C-flex tool & circulate B/U. Perform unofficial casing test to 5000 psi (good test). Open C-flex & take injection pressures. Close C-flex and circulate B/U.

Mon 05/28: Open C-flex & establish injection rates. Perform cement job and squeeze 16.2 ppg Class H cement; 808 cubic feet of cement. Strip up & attempt to close C-flex with no success. Continue attempting to close C-flex. Able to engage & close. Bleed off pressure to confirm closed. Reverse circulate 1.5x string vol. Drop Archer dart & pump down. Attempt to latch into C-flex to permanently lock (no success). Attempt to shear out dart (no success). Pump slug & POOH. 

Tues 05/29: P/U 8-1/2" clean out BHA & RIH 

Wed 05/30: Continue RIH w/ 8-1/2" clean out assy T/ 28;190' & set down 20k. Wash & ream down T/ EZSV at 28;657'. Drill out EZSV. Wash & ream down to landing collar at 29;770' and tag w/ 10k down. Circulate B/U to WH. Function test BOP's & diverter. Continue circulating B/U to surface.

*Verbal approval from Mr. Adriano Garcia regarding BOP stack 1 Yellow Pod

Thurs 05/31: Finish circulating B/U & POOH T/ surface w/ 8-1/2" clean out assembly. R/U Baker wireline & P/U EZSV. RIH w/ EZSV on wireline and set at 29;757' MD/ 27;963' TVD.

Fri 06/01: POOH w/ EZSV setting tool. Test casing to 6500 psi for 30 min (good test). Function UBSR & LBSR. RIH w/ SBT wireline toolstring & perform SBT log. POOH w/ SBT toolstring. RIH w/ 5-7/8" DP to test BOP's.

**Verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson for setting of lockdown bushing

Sat 06/02: Pressure & function test BOP's. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200 psi. Tested rams and all related valves to 250/6500 psi from Halliburton unit with 13.7 ppg surface mud weight (14.06 ppg downhole mud weight) as per TOI procedure monitoring test pressures with EZ chart software. Pressure & function test performed on Yellow Pod from TCP Panel. Function test diverter from DCP. POOH & P/U FMC lock down assy. RIH

***Verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson for TA for THS
"},{"   ":317,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-03","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 06/03: RIH w/ FMC lock down assy. Land out w/ 50k down & pressure up to 7500 psi to set. Take 50k overpull to confirm set. Release FMC RT; POOH; & L/D FMC RT. P/U RTTS assy & RIH w/ 3075' tail pipe below. Set RTTS at 10;685' & perform positive pressure test to 1000 psi (good test). Unable to release from RTTS. Unset RTTS; POOH; & change out overshot.

Mon 06/04: RIH w/ RTTS & set at 10;685'. Release from RTTS & positive test to 1000 psi. Negative test to 200 psi below seawater gradient w/ 197 bbls of base oil. Monitor no flow for 30 minutes. Good test. U-tube base oil out. Displace well above RTTS to seawater. POOH T/ surface w/ RTTS running tool.

Tues 06/05: P/U BLAT tool and transfer weight from MRT's to top drive and unlatch BOP's @ 03:45hrs. Land THS with #2 crane @ 08:30hrs. Unable to get test on THS. Troubleshoot THS test failure.

Wed 06/06:  Continue to troubleshoot THS test failure.

Thurs 06/07:   ROV tested THS connector to 10;300 psi gauge pressure (good test). Land and latch BOP on THS @ 14:36 hrs. P/U RTTS retrieval tool and RIH w/ same. Land FMC tool in THS and test BOP/THS connector against LBSR and UBSR to 250psi low / 9;100psi high. POOH 

Fri 06/08: Finish POOH. RIH w/ Halliburton RTTS overshot T/ 10;650'. Displace seawater above RTTS to 13.7ppg surface wt
SBM while monitoring barrel in / barrel out. Latch onto RTTS; retrieve to surface; and L/D same. POOH 

Sat 06/09: Finish POOH. P/U and M/U Halliburton clean out assemblies and RIH w/ same T/ 26;809'. Function test BOP from TCP on Blue POD. Function test diverter from TCP. 
"},{"   ":318,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-10","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 06/10: Continue RIH w/ Halliburton clean out assembly T/ 29;757'. Tag EZSV @ 29;759'. Displace Choke; Kill; and Boost to 13.9ppg brine to displace well.

*On 06/10/2018 @ 15:15hrs; Mrs. Lisa Lorenz (Shell Regulatory) received approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson (BSEE Houma District) to add negative test of production casing in brine to procedure.

Mon 06/11: Continue displacing well to 13.9ppg CaBr2. POOH w/ WBCO assembly. Observed overpull with MagTech assembly through THS. Pull to surface and recover debris. Continue to POOH.

Tues 06/12:  Finish POOH. RIH with clean out assembly to 29;404' and activate jet sub. Jet BOP and function BOP from DCP on Yellow POD. Re-jet BOP and function diverter from DCP. Drop ball to de-activate jet sub and RIH to tag CIBP at 29;759' DP measurement.

Wed 06/13:  Reverse circulate through HPDU. Perform negative test on production casing by pumping 280 bbls of drill water and pressuring up to 3;000psi differential. Close test rams; bleed off pressure (11 bbls back). Monitor negative pressure test for no flow. Observe no flow from 20:00 to 20:30hrs. Good test. Rig down negative test lines and begin POOH 

Thurs 06/14:   Continue to POOH; Remove debris from magtech and Vali-tech assy; 35lbs of recovered from Vali-tech; 30lbs from magtech. NOTE: recovered chain from chain tongs off tools. Service rig floor equipment and clean same. P/u Halliburton clean well assy and RIH for second clean out run.

Fri 06/15: Continued TIH; Slip & Cut 1;700' of drill line


Sat 06/16: Function BOP's and wash C-flex; Tag bridge plug @ 29757'; Flow check well and POOH; Inspected mag techs and vali techs; R/U wireline

"},{"   ":319,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-17","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 06/17: M/U and RIH with sump packer; Correlate and attempt to set with no success; POOH; Sump packer was pulled back to surface; P/U sump packer and RIH.

Mon 06/18: Continue TIH with sump packer 

Tues 06/19: Set sump packer at 29;475' MD / 27;731' TVD. Pump slug & POOH to test BOP's. Pressure test BOP's from Halliburton unit with 13.9 ppg CaBr2. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200 psi. Tested rams and all related valves to 250/6500 psi. Test performed on Blue Pod from Drillers Panel.

Wed 06/20: Completed BOP testing with 13.9 ppg CaBr2 as per TOI procedure monitoring test pressures with EZ chart software. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200 psi. Tested rams and all related valves to 250/6500 psi. Test
performed on Blue Pod from Drillers Panel; Functioned BOP's and Diverter on 4-1/2" drill pipe from Toolpushers Panel; Yellow Pod.; POOH with sump packer setting tool
 
Thurs 06/21:   R/U to P/U TCP assembly. P/U TCP assembly & RIH on 5-7/8" DP

Fri 06/22: Continue RIH with TCP assembly T/ 29;475'. Snap into sump packer and space out guns. Set packer; Close annular and apply 500 psi on top of packer. Perform firing sequence and observed DP pressure fall off indicating guns fired. Circulate at 2 bpm to establish loss rate (inital 120 bph; decrease to 30 bph). Shut down pumps and open bypass.  Static loss rate of 16 bph. Begin reverse circulation at 3 bpm.

Perfs:
HU1: 27999-28140 MD / 26513-26628 TVD
HU2U: 28248-28389 MD / 26719-26835 TVD
HU2L: 28499-28640 MD / 26925-27041 TVD
HU3: 28751-28892 MD / 27132-27247 TVD
HU4: 29010-29151 MD / 27346-27462 TVD
HU5: 27324-29465 MD / 27606-27721 TVD

Sat 06/23: Finish reverse circulating. Monitor losses (6-8 bbl/hr) and R/D surface iron. POOH w/ TCP assembly circulate. B/U through choke (no gas or contamination observed). Continue POOH 

Losses:  196 bbls
"},{"   ":320,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-24","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 06/24: Continue POOH w/ TCP assy. Close LBSR & boost riser volume while monitoring well on trip tank (6 bbl/hr losses). Continue POOH and L/D TCP assy. P/U deburr BHA & RIH.

Mon 06/25: Continue RIH w/ Deburr BHA to top of perfs. Land out no go locator at 29;617' bit depth. Circulate brine. POOH above perfs & drop Churchill dart. Continue POOH 

Tues 06/26: POOH T/ surface and function test BOP's on 5-7/8" pipe from Toolpusher Control Panel on Blue pod & Diverter from TCP in full auto sequence; on way out.  R/U to run ESTMZ lower completion.

Wed 06/27:  P/U and RIH w/ ESTMZ zones 6; 5; 4; & 3 and pressure test each to 250 psi (all good tests). P/U and RIH w/ ESTMZ zone 2.
 
Thurs 06/28:  P/U & RIH w/ ESTMZ zones 2 & 1 and pressure test each to 250 psi (good tests). RIH w/ 4" wash pipe & latch in STT. POOH w/ 4" wash pipe & pressure test system to 250 psi in sump test position (good test). Confirm space out of lower service tool & pressure test system to 250 psi in RIH position (good test). P/U VCH packer assy; 2 stds of 4-1/2" DP; bundle carrier; 8 stds 5-7/8" DP; & BSRTT assy. RIH on 5-7/8" DP 

Fri 06/29: RIH w/ ESTMZ & BSRTT assy. Land out BSRTT and release. P/U above BOP and pressure test BSR's to 6500 psi. Function BSR's. Retrieve BSRTT and POOH. L/D BSRTT & RIH w/ ESTMZ assy 

Sat 06/30: RIH w/ ESTMZ assy to sump packer. Sting in; sting out to confirm depth. Set VCH packer per procedure BSRITT set at 27;905.71' MD / 26;435' TVD. perform 1500 psi pressure test on backside to confirm set (good test). Set isolation packers per procedure. Pressure test 10-1/8" x 10-3/4" casing for 30 min to 6500 psi (good test). Establish tool positions per Halliburton & pressure test service tool (good test). P/U frac head and R/U frac iron.
"},{"   ":321,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-01","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 07/01: R/U frac iron & test w/ cement unit (good test). Perform pickle job. Pressure test lines again from Stim Star IV to frac head to 14;500 psi (good test). 

Mon 07/02: Perform main frac on zone HU5B. Pull up to zone HU4. test lines to 7;000 psi (good test).

Tues 07/03: Pump frac job for HU4. Early screen out and reverse circulate proppant. Function test BOP from DCP on Yellow POD. Function test diverter from DCP.

***Verbal approval from Mr. Bobby Nelson to proceed with operations with Yellow Pod SEM B HPHT reading inaccuracies

Wed 07/04: Space out and establish tool positions for stimulation of HU3. Perform main frac on zone HU3. 
 
Thurs 07/05: Pull up to zone HU2L Establish tool positions with frac head installed.  Standby while MV Stim Star IV troubleshoots DP issues.

Fri 07/06: Complete troubleshooting/repairs of DP system on frac boat. 

Sat 07/07:  Pump main frac on zone HU2L. Close MCS and test MCS/FCS sleeves to 1;000psi (good test). POOH to zone HU2U. 
"},{"   ":322,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-08","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 07/08: Close MCS and test to 1;000 psi to verify closed. Monitor pressures while cleaning; flushing; and re-filling MGS with 13.9 ppg CaBr2. With LAP closed; open MCS and monitor pressures. Apply 1500 psi to backside and begin bullheading with cement unit at 9 bpm and 3;360 psi. Pumped a total of 1;361 bbls.

Mon 07/09: Continue to bullhead for a total volume of 1;361 bbls. Close MCS and test. Test below zone HU2 (good test) and above zone HU2 (no test). Reverse circulate workstring volume 

Tues 07/10: Pressure test closed MCS to 2;000psi (good test). Monitor pressures while pumping down DS to maintain wellhead pressure. Function test BOPs F/ DCP on Blue POD. Function test Diverter from TCP. 

***Verbal approval to test BOP's on 6" until able to test 4.5" given by Mr. Bobby Nelson

Wed 07/11: Space out to test BOP's on 6-5/8" StimTech joints. Pause testing to run service tool through Zone 1 (HU1) FCS and MJPS and observe TT become static after close shifter passed FCS. Pressure test system to 1;500psi (good test). RIH 2 stands and test well system to 1;500psi (good test). Re-trip MCS and FCS in Zone 2 (HU2U) and pressure test well system to 1;500psi (good test). Pick up side entry sub and rig up test lines. Resume BOP testing.
 
Thurs 07/12: Finish testing BOP's to 250 low /6500 high on both ram and annular and choke manifold. Begin main frac job on HU2U 

Fri 07/13: Complete main frac job on Zone HU2U. Close MCS and test same to 2;500psi.  POOH to zone HU1 and establish tool positions. P/U frac head and install in string. Pressure test surface lines and frac head to 14;500psi. Begin frac job on HU1.

Sat 07/14:  Finish main frac on Zone HU1 as per Halliburton pump schedule. Pressure test closed MCS to 1;500 psi (good test). Begin pressure testing BOP's on 4-1/2" pipe.


"},{"   ":323,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-15","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 07/15: Pressure test BOP's on 4-1/2" DP. Tested annulars and all related valves to 250/4200psi - Rams and all related valves to 250/6500psi from Halliburton unit with 13.9 ppg surface weight and related valves from DCP on Blue POD. Function test BOP from TCP on Blue POD. POOH with ESTMZ service tool F/ 11;457' - T/ surface and L/O same. Hold safety meeting; hang off block; and begin change out of drill line spool.

Mon 07/16:  Pick up and RIH with Halliburton production isolation assembly.

Tues 07/17: Continue RIH w/ Halliburton PIS assembly T/ 26;347'. Landed WBRT at 26;347' bit depth.& sheared out inner mandrel. Observed Fas Fill trip closed & pressure test down string to confirm (good test). Continue RIH T/ 27;892' .

Wed 07/18: RIH & shift open lower completion sleeves while monitoring losses and latch into VCH packer. Pressure test backside to 1000 psi for 30 min (good test). Pressure up down string to 2000 psi to release from PO tool. Reverse circulate 100 bbls to fill string. S/O to re-engage seals into PBR & pressure test FS2 (set at 27;848' MD / 26;387' TVD) down string to 1000 psi for 30 min (good test). Function test BOP's & diverter. POOH & pull wear bushing. Drop activation ball and jet BOP's & THS. Drop deactivation ball & boost riser. POOH F/ 24;484' T/ 5;400'.
 
Thurs 07/19: POOH T/ surface & L/D PO tool. Service rig equipment & R/U Frank's for upper completion. P/U & M/U upper completion assemblies & RIH. P/U CIM assy; terminate; & pressure test (good test). P/U PDPG assy; terminate; & pressure test (good test). RIH w/ production tubing F/ 890' T/ 3;627'.

Fri 07/20: RIH w/ production tubing T/ 3;627' T/ 15;104'. P/U & M/U SCSSV assy; terminate control lines; & pressure test SCSSV with Well Dynamics Unit to 15;000 psi for 15 minutes as per program (good test). RIH w/ production tubing T/ 18;193'. P/U & M/U FMC tubing hanger assy.

Sat 07/21:  Terminate control lines to FMC tubing hanger & test to 15;000 psi for 5 minutes (good test). Pressure test SV1 and SV2 control lines (internal test) to 12;500 psi for 15 minutes (good test). Connected the TEC cable head at bottom of tubing hanger. Pressure tested cable head interface to 15;000 psi for 15 minutes (good test).. P/U THRA. Flush lines & test. RIH w/ spanner joint & connect flat pack lines. Pressure test flat pack to SCSSV to 12;000 psi for 15 minutes. R/U to RIH on landing string. RIH F/ 18;282' T/ 19;538' on landing string.

"},{"   ":324,"WELL_NAME":"SN213","API12":608124012300,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-22","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun 07/22:  Continue RIH w/ upper completion on landing string T/ 27;805'. Land; set; & test tubing hanger seals to 13;100 psi for 15 minutes. No pressure build. Good test. Close SCSSV & pressure test to 500 psi for 15 minutes. no flow; (good test). Open SCSSV; break circulation; & begin packer fluid displacement per program.

Mon 07/23: Finish packer fluid displacement. Set production packer @ 27;313'MD / 25;948' TVD per procedure. Negative test production packer to 5000 psi; Packer's negative test was conducted for 15 minutes and no pressure build method was used. (good test).   Negative test SCSSV to 2750 psi (good test). Positive test production packer to 3000 psi; Hold & chart for 15 minutes(good test). Close AAV and positive test same to 2000 psi (good test). Close SCSSV and monitor no flow for 15 minutes. Open LPR; release THRA from tubing hanger; & P/U to free travel. L/D circulating stand. U-tube 12.0 ppg CaBr2 out from kill line. Displace riser from 13.9 ppg CaBr2 to seawater. POOH w/ THRA F/ 9;588 T/ 6;034'.

Tues 07/24: POOH T/ surface w/ THRA & L/D. R/D Frank's equipment; IWOCS sheave; & Well Dynamics Sheaves. R/U riser equipment on rig floor to unlatch. Pull diverter.

Wed 07/25: R/U riser running tool; P/U landing joint; scope in slip joint & lock in. Transfer weight & unlatch BOP at 03:00 hrs. Move rig to safe zone & make heading change to latch up heading. ROV clean wellhead & prepare tree for land out. Land tree on THS at 10:20 hrs. ROV lock connector & perform pressure test to 9700 psi. ROV remove override tools from tree & align valves on tree. 

**all subsea testing was in PSIG units via ROV (9;611' water depth)

Installation tests are as follows:
1)Gallery Test - 10;050 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes
.	PSV & ASV from Below
.	PMV from Above
2)XT Tree Cap Test - 10;050 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes
.	PSV & ASV from Above
.	XT cap seals and Needle Valves from below
3)PWV Test - 10;300 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes
.	PWV from Below
.	ASV from above
.	PMV from above

Tree connector was tested via an external seal test after the connector was locked.  The connector was tested to 10;425 PSIG subsea / 15 minutes.   
 
Thurs 07/26:  Move rig to safe zone. 

Fri 07/27: Pull BOP on marine riser T/ surface.  *** Operations Complete***
"}]
